1
00:01:35,476 --> 00:01:39,438
Deep among the lonely
sun-baked hills of Texas...

2
00:01:39,316 --> 00:01:43,777
the great and weather-beaten
stone still stands.

3
00:01:43,637 --> 00:01:48,099
The Comanches called it
Squaw's Head Rock.

4
00:01:47,958 --> 00:01:51,419
Time cannot change
its impassive face...

5
00:01:51,319 --> 00:01:54,279
nor dim the legend
of the wild young lovers...

6
00:01:54,199 --> 00:01:59,161
who found heaven and hell
in the shadows of the rock.

7
00:01:58,999 --> 00:02:01,460
For when the sun is low...

8
00:02:01,399 --> 00:02:04,360
and the cold wind blows
across the desert...

9
00:02:04,279 --> 00:02:05,988
there are those
of Indian blood...

10
00:02:05,959 --> 00:02:07,669
who still speak
of Pearl Chavez...

11
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:10,558
the half-breed girl
from down along the border...

12
00:02:10,440 --> 00:02:12,441
and of the laughing outlaw...

13
00:02:12,360 --> 00:02:15,821
with whom she here kept
a final rendezvous...

14
00:02:15,721 --> 00:02:18,723
never to be seen again.

15
00:02:18,601 --> 00:02:21,603
And this is
what the legend says...

16
00:02:21,481 --> 00:02:23,483
A flower known nowhere else...

17
00:02:23,402 --> 00:02:25,903
grows from out
of the desperate crags...

18
00:02:25,801 --> 00:02:27,802
where Pearl vanished...

19
00:02:27,721 --> 00:02:30,723
Pearl, who was herself
a wild flower...

20
00:02:30,601 --> 00:02:35,063
sprung from the hard clay,
quick to blossom...

21
00:02:34,923 --> 00:02:36,924
and early to die.

22
00:03:01,765 --> 00:03:03,475
Pearl.

23
00:03:04,846 --> 00:03:06,598
Where's your ma?

24
00:03:06,566 --> 00:03:08,526
She's in there, dancing.

25
00:03:08,486 --> 00:03:10,947
Like mother, like daughter.

26
00:03:10,887 --> 00:03:14,513
I'm commencing to think
I like the daughter better.

27
00:03:14,407 --> 00:03:16,201
Let go!

28
00:03:16,167 --> 00:03:18,168
You go away from me,
or I'll call my pa.

29
00:03:19,529 --> 00:03:21,488
That renegade creole squaw-man?

30
00:03:21,449 --> 00:03:24,159
That's a rich one.

31
00:03:59,252 --> 00:04:03,756
I'll just raise you
fifty, Mr. Chavez.

32
00:04:03,612 --> 00:04:06,072
Would you mind?

33
00:04:06,014 --> 00:04:07,474
Mind what?

34
00:04:07,454 --> 00:04:10,415
That weed.
I find it rather repulsive.

35
00:04:10,334 --> 00:04:13,295
Pretty fancy gentleman,
ain't you, Mr. Chavez?

36
00:04:13,214 --> 00:04:16,508
He's not so fancy
about his wife, if you ask me.

37
00:04:16,415 --> 00:04:17,999
Look at her.

38
00:05:48,064 --> 00:05:51,191
Quitting? Broke again?

39
00:05:51,104 --> 00:05:52,897
Yes, gentlemen...

40
00:05:52,865 --> 00:05:54,824
but there are
greater tragedies...

41
00:05:54,785 --> 00:05:57,079
that I'm sure
you wouldn't understand.

42
00:06:37,150 --> 00:06:38,275
Pa!

43
00:06:39,510 --> 00:06:41,553
Pa, will you take me
in the Presidio?

44
00:06:41,509 --> 00:06:42,886
I ain't never
been in there and...

45
00:06:42,870 --> 00:06:44,329
And you never should be.

46
00:06:44,311 --> 00:06:47,272
What are you doing out here
at this hour anyway?

47
00:06:47,192 --> 00:06:48,651
I was just dancing.

48
00:06:48,631 --> 00:06:50,091
I've told your mother
repeatedly...

49
00:06:50,072 --> 00:06:52,532
this street is no place
for a girl your age.

50
00:06:52,472 --> 00:06:54,307
I didn't mean no harm.

51
00:06:57,672 --> 00:07:01,132
It's my fault, child, not yours.

52
00:07:01,032 --> 00:07:03,534
The sins of the fathers.

53
00:07:06,314 --> 00:07:08,316
Go home now, dear.

54
00:07:08,235 --> 00:07:10,736
I'll be back in a little while.

55
00:07:32,156 --> 00:07:33,866
Don't! Stop!

56
00:07:33,837 --> 00:07:35,337
No, Chavez! Don't!

57
00:07:37,038 --> 00:07:40,081
Don't! Don't! I beg you! Don't!

58
00:07:43,278 --> 00:07:44,695
Pa!

59
00:07:49,518 --> 00:07:51,519
I plead no mitigating
circumstances.

60
00:07:51,438 --> 00:07:54,440
They deserved to die,
as I deserve to die.

61
00:07:54,319 --> 00:07:56,321
For I long since
killed a person...

62
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:59,699
much superior
to either of them... myself.

63
00:07:59,599 --> 00:08:02,602
I killed that person the day
I gave my family's name...

64
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:05,482
to the woman
who became my wife.

65
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:06,861
And since I believe...

66
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:08,802
the punishment
should fit the crime...

67
00:08:08,721 --> 00:08:11,723
I suggest that you hang me
by the neck until I am dead.

68
00:08:14,962 --> 00:08:17,464
It's from Laura Belle.

69
00:08:17,362 --> 00:08:20,155
Did I ever tell you about her?

70
00:08:20,082 --> 00:08:21,916
She's my second cousin.

71
00:08:23,762 --> 00:08:25,846
Yes, Laura Belle
is my second cousin...

72
00:08:25,802 --> 00:08:28,971
but she was
more than that to me.

73
00:08:28,883 --> 00:08:33,845
You see, once upon a time,
in a different age...

74
00:08:33,684 --> 00:08:38,478
in a different age
and such a different world...

75
00:08:38,324 --> 00:08:40,450
I was in love.

76
00:08:40,404 --> 00:08:43,573
And wonderful to believe,
the lady was in love with me.

77
00:08:44,885 --> 00:08:47,178
You mustn't look at me
as though that were impossible.

78
00:08:47,125 --> 00:08:50,043
I was quite the looker
in my day and very dashing.

79
00:08:49,965 --> 00:08:53,926
Perhaps a bit too dashing.

80
00:08:53,805 --> 00:08:57,266
And that's why
this very wonderful girl...

81
00:08:57,165 --> 00:09:03,128
who might have been your mother,
decided on security...

82
00:09:02,926 --> 00:09:05,887
and gave herself in wedlock
to a wealthy yankee.

83
00:09:05,847 --> 00:09:07,307
Better make it fast, Chavez.

84
00:09:07,288 --> 00:09:08,705
You've only got
five minutes left.

85
00:09:08,686 --> 00:09:10,522
No! No!

86
00:09:11,727 --> 00:09:13,271
They can't.

87
00:09:13,247 --> 00:09:15,957
They can't. I won't let them.

88
00:09:15,888 --> 00:09:17,848
Better that it end.

89
00:09:17,808 --> 00:09:19,684
Really it is.

90
00:09:21,648 --> 00:09:24,275
Your mother and I
can't hurt you any longer.

91
00:09:24,208 --> 00:09:27,003
Laura Belle wants
my little girl to go to her.

92
00:09:26,930 --> 00:09:28,889
Yes, just a few more weeks...

93
00:09:28,850 --> 00:09:30,809
and at last,
you'll have a home...

94
00:09:30,770 --> 00:09:32,688
the mother you should have had.

95
00:09:34,130 --> 00:09:36,591
No, you mustn't leave me.
You mustn't.

96
00:09:37,970 --> 00:09:39,929
You've been a good child.

97
00:09:39,890 --> 00:09:41,850
Through some miracle,
you're good...

98
00:09:41,811 --> 00:09:44,271
and you're decent,
and you're strong.

99
00:09:44,211 --> 00:09:47,171
And now you must prove
that you are strong.

100
00:09:47,092 --> 00:09:49,968
You will do that for me,
won't you, darling?

101
00:09:49,892 --> 00:09:52,353
No tears, no grief...

102
00:09:52,292 --> 00:09:54,794
now or later.

103
00:09:57,412 --> 00:10:00,498
Here. Keep this scarf.

104
00:10:02,372 --> 00:10:04,332
Wear it sometimes.

105
00:10:04,293 --> 00:10:06,961
Get her out of here, Chavez.

106
00:10:06,893 --> 00:10:10,145
Listen to me, darling.
We've very little time.

107
00:10:10,054 --> 00:10:13,014
I want you to lean
on Laura Belle...

108
00:10:12,935 --> 00:10:15,395
make her your inspiration
and your guide.

109
00:10:15,335 --> 00:10:18,295
And then one day,
you'll be the great lady...

110
00:10:18,215 --> 00:10:21,175
I've always wanted you to be.

111
00:10:21,095 --> 00:10:23,555
Promise me that.

112
00:10:23,496 --> 00:10:24,955
I promise.

113
00:10:24,936 --> 00:10:26,437
Cross your heart?

114
00:10:27,816 --> 00:10:29,275
Cross my heart.

115
00:10:29,256 --> 00:10:31,215
She'll love you.
I know she will.

116
00:10:31,176 --> 00:10:35,096
And you must give her
all the love you've had for me.

117
00:10:41,738 --> 00:10:44,698
Smile for me.

118
00:10:44,618 --> 00:10:48,079
Now, now. Head high.

119
00:10:49,377 --> 00:10:51,588
Strong.

120
00:10:53,218 --> 00:10:56,179
Very strong.

121
00:11:06,180 --> 00:11:09,140
All threats of hell
and hopes of paradise...

122
00:11:09,060 --> 00:11:11,520
one thing at least
is certain...

123
00:11:11,461 --> 00:11:13,421
this life flies.

124
00:11:13,382 --> 00:11:17,300
One thing is certain,
and the rest is lies.

125
00:11:17,222 --> 00:11:22,643
The flower that once
has bloomed forever dies.

126
00:11:22,503 --> 00:11:24,462
Ready, Chavez?

127
00:11:24,422 --> 00:11:26,382
Quite ready, sheriff.

128
00:11:41,225 --> 00:11:42,183
Whoa!

129
00:11:48,825 --> 00:11:51,785
I beg your pardon.

130
00:11:51,705 --> 00:11:54,166
You can't be...
What's your name?

131
00:11:54,106 --> 00:11:56,107
None of your business.

132
00:11:57,946 --> 00:11:59,447
Sorry.

133
00:12:02,748 --> 00:12:05,708
I really am sorry.
I wonder if I could...

134
00:12:05,628 --> 00:12:08,588
I don't talk to no strangers.

135
00:12:08,508 --> 00:12:12,969
That's a good rule generally,
I grant you, but...

136
00:12:12,828 --> 00:12:14,829
in this case, it...

137
00:12:16,667 --> 00:12:18,127
Come on.

138
00:12:18,108 --> 00:12:20,067
Won't you answer
just one question?

139
00:12:20,028 --> 00:12:21,487
What is it?

140
00:12:21,468 --> 00:12:23,094
Did you see
a little southern tot...

141
00:12:23,068 --> 00:12:24,528
on the Guadalupe coach?

142
00:12:24,509 --> 00:12:25,510
No.

143
00:12:26,909 --> 00:12:28,870
Are you sure?
She was traveling alone.

144
00:12:28,830 --> 00:12:30,623
You said "one question."

145
00:12:30,590 --> 00:12:33,049
I know, but it doesn't
seem unreasonable if you...

146
00:12:32,990 --> 00:12:34,950
Now you go away
and leave me alone.

147
00:12:34,910 --> 00:12:36,869
I know all about men like you.

148
00:12:36,830 --> 00:12:38,332
Well...

149
00:12:39,710 --> 00:12:41,128
Good morning.

150
00:12:42,511 --> 00:12:44,513
Why couldn't they have been
a little more explicit...

151
00:12:44,432 --> 00:12:46,433
about just which coach
they were sending her on?

152
00:12:46,351 --> 00:12:47,852
Don't worry, Jesse.

153
00:12:47,791 --> 00:12:50,084
I'll drive her out to the ranch
whenever she shows up.

154
00:12:50,033 --> 00:12:51,533
Thanks, Lem.
You can't miss her.

155
00:12:51,472 --> 00:12:52,974
She's one of those...

156
00:12:52,913 --> 00:12:54,413
well-brought-up
southern children.

157
00:12:54,352 --> 00:12:55,979
Probably be hungry
and crying her eyes out.

158
00:12:55,953 --> 00:12:58,955
I'll give her some milk
and blow her nose for her.

159
00:12:58,833 --> 00:13:00,334
Thanks again.

160
00:13:01,393 --> 00:13:02,895
And... so long!

161
00:13:02,834 --> 00:13:04,459
So long.

162
00:13:04,433 --> 00:13:07,393
Give my regards to the old man.

163
00:13:07,313 --> 00:13:09,482
I will.

164
00:13:09,434 --> 00:13:12,395
Say hello to Laura Belle for me.

165
00:13:12,275 --> 00:13:13,775
Wait!

166
00:13:14,995 --> 00:13:18,831
Wait! Do you know
somebody named Laura Belle?

167
00:13:19,955 --> 00:13:23,416
I said, do you know
somebody named Laura Belle?

168
00:13:23,315 --> 00:13:24,817
None of your business.

169
00:13:24,756 --> 00:13:26,256
It is my business.

170
00:13:26,195 --> 00:13:27,989
I don't talk to no strangers.

171
00:13:27,956 --> 00:13:29,749
You can answer
one question, can't you?

172
00:13:29,716 --> 00:13:31,259
That won't hurt you none.

173
00:13:31,237 --> 00:13:34,197
All right, one question.
But remember, just one.

174
00:13:34,118 --> 00:13:35,827
I know all about girls like you.

175
00:13:35,797 --> 00:13:38,299
Don't you dare say that.

176
00:13:38,197 --> 00:13:39,615
Pearl.

177
00:13:39,598 --> 00:13:41,307
How'd you know my name?

178
00:13:41,277 --> 00:13:42,987
If you hadn't been so uppity...

179
00:13:42,958 --> 00:13:45,084
I'd have known who you were
a long time ago.

180
00:13:45,038 --> 00:13:46,665
Now come on. Get in.

181
00:13:46,638 --> 00:13:48,097
Who are you?

182
00:13:48,078 --> 00:13:49,871
My mother couldn't come
to meet you...

183
00:13:49,839 --> 00:13:51,298
so I came in her place.

184
00:13:51,278 --> 00:13:54,072
I'm Laura Belle's son...
the older one, Jesse.

185
00:13:53,999 --> 00:13:55,041
There.

186
00:14:12,242 --> 00:14:15,202
I'm sorry about
not recognizing you.

187
00:14:15,122 --> 00:14:17,581
I guess your clothes
sort of fooled me.

188
00:14:17,521 --> 00:14:19,981
Don't misunderstand me.
I think they're beautiful.

189
00:14:19,923 --> 00:14:21,382
You do?

190
00:14:21,363 --> 00:14:24,323
Yes, and very unusual.
But you know...

191
00:14:24,243 --> 00:14:26,703
I think I'd like to see you
in brighter colors.

192
00:14:26,643 --> 00:14:28,602
Like green?
I have a green blouse.

193
00:14:28,563 --> 00:14:31,190
- Green, blue, yellow maybe.
- Yellow?

194
00:14:31,124 --> 00:14:33,083
I have a real pretty
yellow one right here.

195
00:14:33,043 --> 00:14:36,587
- I'll put it on now.
- Not now.

196
00:14:36,484 --> 00:14:38,902
Save it for tomorrow.

197
00:14:51,525 --> 00:14:53,485
Here's where the ranch starts.

198
00:14:53,445 --> 00:14:58,116
There's the marker...
the Spanish Bit...

199
00:14:57,966 --> 00:15:00,218
a million acres
of McCanles empire.

200
00:15:00,166 --> 00:15:02,627
Empire? Isn't this still Texas?

201
00:15:02,567 --> 00:15:06,319
Yes, but the Senator doesn't
always acknowledge that. Look.

202
00:15:06,207 --> 00:15:08,626
He puts his seal
of ownership on everything.

203
00:15:08,568 --> 00:15:10,778
It's on his sons, too,
I suppose.

204
00:15:10,728 --> 00:15:12,688
In fact, I'm sure
my brother Lewt and I...

205
00:15:12,647 --> 00:15:14,608
are the Senator's
favorite property.

206
00:15:14,568 --> 00:15:17,529
Is your brother as nice
as you are?

207
00:15:17,448 --> 00:15:19,866
Girls in town think he's nicer.

208
00:15:21,129 --> 00:15:23,756
- Hiya, Jesse.
- Howdy, Jake.

209
00:15:23,689 --> 00:15:26,190
Fine foals.

210
00:15:33,731 --> 00:15:36,357
Is that your house?

211
00:15:36,291 --> 00:15:38,125
That is the residence

212
00:15:38,091 --> 00:15:40,676
of Jackson Tilt McCanles
and family.

213
00:15:40,610 --> 00:15:44,989
And on to the fortress...
and happiness.

214
00:16:02,693 --> 00:16:05,987
Jesse! Pearl!

215
00:16:20,296 --> 00:16:21,755
Here you are.

216
00:16:21,736 --> 00:16:24,696
Prettiest girl ever to set foot
on Spanish Bit.

217
00:16:25,936 --> 00:16:27,437
Pearl, dear.

218
00:16:28,456 --> 00:16:30,540
I'm so glad you've
come to us, darling.

219
00:16:30,496 --> 00:16:33,249
Here, let me look at you.

220
00:16:33,177 --> 00:16:35,720
Yes, you're Scott's daughter.

221
00:16:35,657 --> 00:16:37,158
And now you're ours.

222
00:16:37,098 --> 00:16:38,808
You're just like he said.

223
00:16:38,778 --> 00:16:41,405
I'm afraid I'm somewhat
different than he remembered.

224
00:16:41,338 --> 00:16:42,839
But come, dear.

225
00:16:42,819 --> 00:16:44,737
Did you take good care
of her, Jesse?

226
00:16:44,698 --> 00:16:46,658
I showed her all
the points of interest.

227
00:16:46,618 --> 00:16:49,579
- He did. He's nice.
- I think so, too.

228
00:16:49,498 --> 00:16:51,417
You southern belles
are all alike.

229
00:16:52,859 --> 00:16:55,320
Where in holleration
you been all day?

230
00:16:55,259 --> 00:16:57,052
I just went down
to Paradise Flats.

231
00:16:57,019 --> 00:16:59,855
- Senator, this is Pearl.
- Who?

232
00:16:59,780 --> 00:17:01,198
Pearl Chavez, our cousin.

233
00:17:01,181 --> 00:17:03,516
You remember. We invited her
to come and stay with us.

234
00:17:03,460 --> 00:17:06,629
Don't be scared.
You're not a trespasser.

235
00:17:06,541 --> 00:17:08,876
She's no cousin of mine.

236
00:17:08,820 --> 00:17:10,656
She's Scott Chavez's
daughter, ain't she?

237
00:17:10,621 --> 00:17:12,581
Yes, of course she is.

238
00:17:12,541 --> 00:17:15,168
Why don't you say so?

239
00:17:15,102 --> 00:17:19,480
Girl, what are you doing
in that getup?

240
00:17:19,342 --> 00:17:21,301
Is that the latest fashion...

241
00:17:21,262 --> 00:17:25,140
with them aristocratic
cousins of yours?

242
00:17:25,023 --> 00:17:29,735
Or is it what they're
wearing this season in wigwams?

243
00:17:32,423 --> 00:17:34,508
Come on, boy.
We got to talk business.

244
00:17:34,463 --> 00:17:35,923
See you later, Pearl.

245
00:17:35,904 --> 00:17:39,031
Come, dear.
I'll take you to your room.

246
00:17:38,945 --> 00:17:40,404
He don't want me here.

247
00:17:40,384 --> 00:17:43,345
You mustn't mind the Senator.
He doesn't mean anything by it.

248
00:17:43,264 --> 00:17:45,225
It's his way ever since...

249
00:17:45,185 --> 00:17:47,145
ever since his accident.

250
00:17:47,105 --> 00:17:48,565
Accident?

251
00:17:48,546 --> 00:17:50,005
It's a long story...

252
00:17:49,985 --> 00:17:51,946
and, I'm afraid,
not a very pleasant one.

253
00:17:51,905 --> 00:17:53,866
I wish we had
a better room for you...

254
00:17:53,826 --> 00:17:56,620
but later on,
we'll speak to the Senator.

255
00:17:56,547 --> 00:17:58,714
Lewton, dear.

256
00:18:01,347 --> 00:18:05,016
This is Pearl.
My youngest son... Lewton.

257
00:18:06,867 --> 00:18:10,203
Pleased to meet you, Lewton.

258
00:18:10,109 --> 00:18:13,111
Pleased to meet you...

259
00:18:13,028 --> 00:18:14,404
Pearl.

260
00:18:15,749 --> 00:18:17,249
Come, Pearl.

261
00:18:17,228 --> 00:18:19,814
You and Lewton will have
plenty of time later on...

262
00:18:19,749 --> 00:18:21,959
to get to know one another.

263
00:18:21,909 --> 00:18:25,161
I'm sure we will.

264
00:18:29,709 --> 00:18:33,670
Yay... boy.

265
00:18:40,311 --> 00:18:43,439
Sounds of the rude world

266
00:18:43,351 --> 00:18:46,937
Heard in the day

267
00:18:46,832 --> 00:18:49,000
Lulled by the moonlight

268
00:18:48,951 --> 00:18:53,288
Have all passed away

269
00:18:54,554 --> 00:18:58,389
Beautiful dreamer

270
00:18:58,274 --> 00:19:01,818
Queen of my song

271
00:19:01,713 --> 00:19:05,383
List' while I woo thee...

272
00:19:05,273 --> 00:19:08,276
Where will I put
your medicine, Mrs. McCanles?

273
00:19:08,154 --> 00:19:10,655
Leave it on the table.

274
00:19:11,995 --> 00:19:14,997
Mrs. McCanles,
can I get married?

275
00:19:14,875 --> 00:19:17,334
But, Vashti, whom do
you want to marry?

276
00:19:17,275 --> 00:19:19,277
Nobody in particular, ma'am.

277
00:19:19,196 --> 00:19:22,198
I just thought I'd kind of
like to get married.

278
00:19:22,076 --> 00:19:23,577
Of course, Vashti.

279
00:19:23,516 --> 00:19:25,434
You may marry
whenever you wish.

280
00:19:25,397 --> 00:19:27,356
Thank you, ma'am.

281
00:19:28,757 --> 00:19:30,216
Do you know anybody...

282
00:19:30,197 --> 00:19:32,199
who would be nice
for me to marry?

283
00:19:33,597 --> 00:19:36,808
No, I don't,
but I'll think about it.

284
00:19:36,717 --> 00:19:38,885
Thank you, ma'am.

285
00:19:38,838 --> 00:19:41,382
There's no particular hurry.

286
00:19:41,319 --> 00:19:43,195
That Vashti.

287
00:19:43,158 --> 00:19:46,452
I'm afraid I'll never be able
to train her properly.

288
00:19:46,359 --> 00:19:48,026
And as to marriage...

289
00:19:49,879 --> 00:19:51,505
Sit down.

290
00:19:51,479 --> 00:19:54,148
I'm glad your father
sent you to me.

291
00:19:54,080 --> 00:19:56,665
All you have to do
is behave like a lady.

292
00:19:56,599 --> 00:19:58,559
Not that
Scott Chavez's daughter...

293
00:19:58,519 --> 00:20:00,479
could ever be anything
but a lady.

294
00:20:00,439 --> 00:20:02,400
I'm a good girl, ma'am.

295
00:20:02,361 --> 00:20:06,989
Of course you are, dear,
but you see...

296
00:20:06,841 --> 00:20:10,135
you'll be the only young girl
at Spanish Bit.

297
00:20:10,041 --> 00:20:11,668
No one could blame you...

298
00:20:11,642 --> 00:20:13,351
if your head
were turned a little.

299
00:20:13,321 --> 00:20:15,866
You take Lewton, for instance.

300
00:20:15,802 --> 00:20:18,262
He's such an attractive boy.

301
00:20:18,202 --> 00:20:20,161
I think Jesse's much nicer.

302
00:20:20,122 --> 00:20:22,332
But you scarcely know Lewton.

303
00:20:22,282 --> 00:20:24,408
Of course, he's
a bit undisciplined...

304
00:20:24,363 --> 00:20:27,824
but perhaps that's what gives
westerners their charm.

305
00:20:27,723 --> 00:20:30,183
The Senator was like that.

306
00:20:30,124 --> 00:20:32,542
That's why, when your father...

307
00:20:33,964 --> 00:20:37,925
Jesse always chides me
for talking about the past.

308
00:20:37,805 --> 00:20:39,431
I hope Jesse likes me.

309
00:20:39,404 --> 00:20:41,198
We're going to lose him someday.

310
00:20:41,163 --> 00:20:44,624
I've known that ever since
he came back from law school.

311
00:20:44,524 --> 00:20:46,151
I've been so selfish.

312
00:20:46,125 --> 00:20:49,920
He'd have gone long ago
if it weren't for me.

313
00:20:49,806 --> 00:20:52,767
My firstborn... he's so good.

314
00:20:52,686 --> 00:20:56,648
He's made such
a difference in my life.

315
00:20:56,526 --> 00:20:59,654
- Ma'am?
- Yes, Pearl?

316
00:20:59,567 --> 00:21:01,860
I'll be a good girl.

317
00:21:01,807 --> 00:21:04,267
I promise I will.

318
00:21:04,206 --> 00:21:06,666
I want to be like you.

319
00:21:06,607 --> 00:21:09,567
That's what my father wanted.

320
00:21:09,487 --> 00:21:12,448
I'm afraid neither
your father nor I...

321
00:21:12,369 --> 00:21:14,328
found happiness, child.

322
00:21:14,289 --> 00:21:16,791
I hope you will.

323
00:21:19,048 --> 00:21:21,009
Come, child.

324
00:21:20,969 --> 00:21:23,429
This is no way to begin.

325
00:21:23,369 --> 00:21:25,745
Do you know this waltz?

326
00:21:29,609 --> 00:21:33,904
Will you stop
that infernal instrument!

327
00:21:33,771 --> 00:21:35,563
King me, Senator.

328
00:21:35,531 --> 00:21:39,242
I always figured when I moved
into my own quarters...

329
00:21:39,131 --> 00:21:40,632
I'd be rid of that noise.

330
00:21:40,652 --> 00:21:42,611
I guess that's it, Senator.

331
00:21:42,572 --> 00:21:45,032
I think I'll take me
a little stroll.

332
00:21:44,971 --> 00:21:48,390
Now we got that papoose
to put up with.

333
00:21:48,332 --> 00:21:50,291
I don't know.

334
00:21:50,252 --> 00:21:52,588
She looks like
a pretty cute tamale to me.

335
00:21:52,532 --> 00:21:55,993
You think so?
Wouldn't appeal to me none.

336
00:21:55,894 --> 00:22:00,146
Of course, I always
liked my women more...

337
00:22:00,014 --> 00:22:03,308
Say, Senator.

338
00:22:03,213 --> 00:22:04,673
Yeah, Lewt?

339
00:22:04,654 --> 00:22:06,613
You know that last trip
I took up to Abilene?

340
00:22:06,574 --> 00:22:07,700
Yeah.

341
00:22:07,695 --> 00:22:10,989
I was driving the herd all day
and kind of tired...

342
00:22:10,894 --> 00:22:12,854
and felt like getting
some relaxation.

343
00:22:12,814 --> 00:22:14,775
Yeah. Didn't happen
to drop into a place...

344
00:22:14,735 --> 00:22:16,611
called the Last Chance, did you?

345
00:22:16,575 --> 00:22:18,534
How did you find that out?

346
00:22:18,496 --> 00:22:20,957
Sent them a check
for 1,600 just yesterday.

347
00:22:20,896 --> 00:22:22,856
That's how I found out.

348
00:22:22,816 --> 00:22:26,277
I guess I had
a few drinks too many.

349
00:22:26,177 --> 00:22:28,136
That's all right.

350
00:22:28,096 --> 00:22:31,056
A fella's got to sow
some wild oats sometime.

351
00:22:30,977 --> 00:22:32,937
What's the money for?

352
00:22:32,897 --> 00:22:34,856
Senator...

353
00:22:34,817 --> 00:22:37,194
I hope someday I'll be like you.

354
00:22:39,137 --> 00:22:43,099
The only thing
I don't like about you...

355
00:22:42,979 --> 00:22:45,439
is the miserable way
you play poker.

356
00:22:45,379 --> 00:22:49,840
Trying to fill inside straights
is a sucker's game.

357
00:22:49,698 --> 00:22:52,701
Go on, boy. Go on. Run along.

358
00:22:55,140 --> 00:22:57,808
What a boy.

359
00:23:06,781 --> 00:23:10,200
How'd they come
to name you Pearl?

360
00:23:10,102 --> 00:23:12,144
I don't know, sir.

361
00:23:12,101 --> 00:23:15,270
Couldn't have had
much eye for color, could they?

362
00:23:17,462 --> 00:23:23,967
They might better have called
you Pocahontas or Minnehaha.

363
00:23:23,743 --> 00:23:25,286
Ain't that right?

364
00:23:25,262 --> 00:23:28,056
I guess so.

365
00:23:27,983 --> 00:23:30,985
All right, Minne, on your way.

366
00:23:30,904 --> 00:23:33,407
Good night, sir.

367
00:23:33,305 --> 00:23:36,098
Minne... ha ha.

368
00:23:36,025 --> 00:23:38,151
Ha ha.

369
00:23:38,105 --> 00:23:40,106
Hello, Pearl. What's the matter?

370
00:23:40,025 --> 00:23:43,527
Are you unhappy?
Don't you like Spanish Bit?

371
00:23:44,865 --> 00:23:46,825
If everybody was like you.

372
00:23:46,745 --> 00:23:48,747
If everybody was like me,
the world would be...

373
00:23:48,666 --> 00:23:50,667
a terribly frustrated
sort of place.

374
00:23:50,587 --> 00:23:52,046
What do you mean?

375
00:23:52,027 --> 00:23:55,029
Nothing for you to worry
your pretty little head about.

376
00:23:54,907 --> 00:23:56,908
I want to learn.
Will you learn me?

377
00:23:56,827 --> 00:23:58,828
Your ma says you're a lawyer.

378
00:23:58,746 --> 00:24:01,749
I want to be a lady
and know everything, like her.

379
00:24:01,627 --> 00:24:04,629
I wonder if learning
ever made mother any happier.

380
00:24:04,508 --> 00:24:07,010
- I wish I could do that.
- What?

381
00:24:06,908 --> 00:24:09,367
Make rings like that.
Can I try? Let me try.

382
00:24:09,307 --> 00:24:11,725
No, Pearl. Now whoa.

383
00:24:11,668 --> 00:24:13,628
Ladies aren't supposed to smoke.

384
00:24:15,509 --> 00:24:18,469
Now you won't want
to learn me things, will you?

385
00:24:18,389 --> 00:24:20,849
You don't like me
no more, do you?

386
00:24:20,789 --> 00:24:23,250
Of course I do.

387
00:24:25,110 --> 00:24:28,571
I'm afraid a lot of men
will want to learn you things.

388
00:24:33,269 --> 00:24:35,730
I think you better go to bed...

389
00:24:35,672 --> 00:24:37,631
like a good little girl.

390
00:24:39,671 --> 00:24:42,965
We'll discuss your education
another time.

391
00:24:42,871 --> 00:24:44,832
All right.

392
00:24:44,792 --> 00:24:46,752
Good night, Pearl.

393
00:24:46,712 --> 00:24:48,673
Good night, Jesse.

394
00:25:03,715 --> 00:25:05,507
Good night.

395
00:25:34,158 --> 00:25:36,159
What do you want?

396
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:54,360
I hate you!

397
00:25:54,321 --> 00:25:57,281
Don't you pretend
nobody ever did that before.

398
00:25:57,201 --> 00:26:00,536
They didn't. Nobody did.
Nobody's going to.

399
00:26:01,680 --> 00:26:03,015
You little...

400
00:26:09,963 --> 00:26:11,505
You leave that alone!

401
00:26:12,843 --> 00:26:14,969
I reckon he must be
the white half.

402
00:26:18,922 --> 00:26:22,258
I forgot to say
good night, ma'am.

403
00:26:30,124 --> 00:26:34,752
Sometimes I feel like
a motherless child

404
00:26:34,605 --> 00:26:39,900
That ain't no ham, Miss Pearl.
That's a pig.

405
00:26:39,725 --> 00:26:41,351
Same thing.

406
00:26:41,325 --> 00:26:43,785
But Mrs. McCanles,
she's very particular...

407
00:26:43,725 --> 00:26:48,645
and she don't want no big pig
listed like no little ham.

408
00:26:48,525 --> 00:26:50,986
Here. Maybe you better
make the list, Vashti.

409
00:26:50,926 --> 00:26:52,885
No, ma'am. I can't write.

410
00:26:52,847 --> 00:26:56,767
Mrs. McCanles says to me once,
"Vashti, can you write?"

411
00:26:56,687 --> 00:26:58,646
And I says, "Mrs. McCanles..."

412
00:26:58,607 --> 00:27:00,566
Vashti.

413
00:27:00,527 --> 00:27:03,655
Mrs. McCanles says to me once,
"Vashti, can you write?"

414
00:27:03,567 --> 00:27:05,360
And I says, "Mrs. McCanles..."

415
00:27:05,328 --> 00:27:06,787
Vashti!

416
00:27:06,768 --> 00:27:08,227
Mrs. McCanles says...

417
00:27:08,208 --> 00:27:09,668
Vashti!

418
00:27:09,649 --> 00:27:12,275
That's Mr. Lewt.
I think he wants to see me.

419
00:27:12,208 --> 00:27:13,625
Vashti, where are you?

420
00:27:13,608 --> 00:27:16,443
I'm scared of that Mr. Lewt.

421
00:27:16,369 --> 00:27:19,788
He says to me once,
"Vashti, you're empty-headed."

422
00:27:19,729 --> 00:27:20,688
Vashti!

423
00:27:20,690 --> 00:27:22,649
Tell Miss Pearl
to come out here.

424
00:27:22,609 --> 00:27:23,902
Miss Pearl...

425
00:27:23,890 --> 00:27:26,683
I heard him. Tell him I'm busy.

426
00:27:26,610 --> 00:27:28,070
Why don't you tell him...

427
00:27:28,050 --> 00:27:29,759
and I'll just run along
up to the house?

428
00:27:29,730 --> 00:27:32,106
All right, I'll tell him.

429
00:27:33,491 --> 00:27:34,949
What do you want?

430
00:27:34,930 --> 00:27:37,558
Thought you might like
to see some tricks.

431
00:27:37,493 --> 00:27:38,951
Watch this.

432
00:27:42,612 --> 00:27:44,738
That's a good boy.

433
00:27:56,293 --> 00:27:57,794
Hey, Lewt.

434
00:27:58,854 --> 00:28:00,104
What do you want?

435
00:28:00,093 --> 00:28:02,345
I thought you were supposed to
be on the round-up today.

436
00:28:02,295 --> 00:28:04,171
And suppose you tend
to your mortgages...

437
00:28:04,134 --> 00:28:06,761
and stop sticking your nose
in my business.

438
00:28:06,695 --> 00:28:09,114
Just as one civilized man
to another, l...

439
00:28:09,055 --> 00:28:10,556
if that isn't insulting you...

440
00:28:10,535 --> 00:28:12,495
I have a little
suggestion to make.

441
00:28:12,456 --> 00:28:14,415
All right. Let's have it.

442
00:28:14,376 --> 00:28:17,586
Why don't you
leave this one alone?

443
00:28:17,496 --> 00:28:20,581
She may do very nicely
if given half a chance.

444
00:28:21,736 --> 00:28:23,695
What's the matter, judge?

445
00:28:23,657 --> 00:28:26,492
You got her earmarked
for yourself?

446
00:28:35,218 --> 00:28:36,678
Hey, Pearl.

447
00:28:37,897 --> 00:28:40,358
Come on, Dice. Push.

448
00:28:40,299 --> 00:28:42,341
Whoa.

449
00:28:42,298 --> 00:28:44,466
Give me a good push.

450
00:28:47,099 --> 00:28:50,019
Whoa, boy.
I want you to meet a lady.

451
00:28:51,620 --> 00:28:54,497
Now bow for the lady, Dice.

452
00:28:57,580 --> 00:28:59,498
He's right smart.

453
00:29:01,301 --> 00:29:04,678
What do you think
of my new girl, Dice?

454
00:29:06,621 --> 00:29:09,623
Oh? Maybe not.

455
00:29:09,502 --> 00:29:11,921
Did you teach him all that?

456
00:29:14,143 --> 00:29:15,602
All that and lots more.

457
00:29:15,582 --> 00:29:17,376
He'll turn on a dime
and give you change.

458
00:29:17,343 --> 00:29:20,345
- Do you want to try him?
- Me ride him?

459
00:29:20,223 --> 00:29:21,681
You're just having fun with me.

460
00:29:21,662 --> 00:29:23,122
Or can't you ride bareback?

461
00:29:23,103 --> 00:29:25,896
- Of course I can.
- Let me see you.

462
00:29:25,823 --> 00:29:28,157
I could show you,
but I got work to do.

463
00:29:28,103 --> 00:29:31,731
Of course, if you don't dare,
I don't give a doggone.

464
00:29:35,585 --> 00:29:37,711
Yeah?

465
00:29:37,664 --> 00:29:39,291
Get off him.

466
00:29:39,265 --> 00:29:41,266
Sure enough. He won't throw you.

467
00:29:41,185 --> 00:29:43,187
He's smooth as cream.

468
00:29:49,346 --> 00:29:51,347
Come on!

469
00:29:53,226 --> 00:29:55,186
Now git!

470
00:30:13,628 --> 00:30:15,171
Open the gate!

471
00:31:02,154 --> 00:31:03,697
You all right?

472
00:31:09,875 --> 00:31:12,335
That was a fool thing to say.

473
00:31:12,276 --> 00:31:15,695
You never rode bareback
before in your life.

474
00:31:16,916 --> 00:31:20,293
I never said I had.

475
00:31:20,196 --> 00:31:22,072
Is she hurt, Lewt?

476
00:31:22,036 --> 00:31:23,662
No. Get out of here.

477
00:31:23,637 --> 00:31:25,096
Can we do anything?

478
00:31:25,076 --> 00:31:27,203
Go on and mosey, will you?

479
00:31:27,157 --> 00:31:29,660
Sure.

480
00:31:35,479 --> 00:31:38,439
You got gumption,
but you ain't got no sense.

481
00:31:38,359 --> 00:31:40,151
If you'd only let me
start him right...

482
00:31:40,118 --> 00:31:42,078
instead of scaring him that way.

483
00:31:42,039 --> 00:31:43,998
It wasn't him that was scared.

484
00:31:43,959 --> 00:31:45,918
He won't throw me next time.

485
00:31:45,878 --> 00:31:47,671
You better stick
to buggy-riding.

486
00:31:47,639 --> 00:31:49,765
Maybe him and me
ain't your style.

487
00:31:49,720 --> 00:31:52,138
Ain't no maybe about you.

488
00:31:52,080 --> 00:31:54,040
I wish you'd let me
ride him some more.

489
00:31:54,001 --> 00:31:55,751
Sure.

490
00:31:55,720 --> 00:31:57,680
How'd you like me
to give him to you?

491
00:31:57,641 --> 00:32:00,309
You mean for keeps?
You're not just teasing?

492
00:32:00,241 --> 00:32:02,200
No. I guess you'd
rather have Jesse...

493
00:32:02,160 --> 00:32:03,787
pick you out a riding horse...

494
00:32:03,761 --> 00:32:05,554
even if he don't know
the difference...

495
00:32:05,521 --> 00:32:07,481
between a pinto
and a strawberry roan.

496
00:32:07,442 --> 00:32:08,900
I like this one.

497
00:32:08,881 --> 00:32:10,840
And you like me,
don't you, honey?

498
00:32:10,801 --> 00:32:12,761
You won't throw me no more.

499
00:32:12,723 --> 00:32:15,016
All right. He's yours.

500
00:32:22,483 --> 00:32:25,777
Let's you and me ride down
to the sump after supper, huh?

501
00:32:25,684 --> 00:32:27,142
Where's that?

502
00:32:27,123 --> 00:32:30,083
A shady place
over by Hidden Canyon.

503
00:32:30,003 --> 00:32:34,131
The water's good and deep now,
almost over your head.

504
00:32:34,005 --> 00:32:36,632
You mean go swimming... together?

505
00:32:36,565 --> 00:32:39,859
I'll bring along my guitar,
play us some music.

506
00:32:39,765 --> 00:32:41,225
You got a nerve.

507
00:32:41,206 --> 00:32:43,498
The moon will be
pretty near full.

508
00:32:43,445 --> 00:32:46,405
You didn't buy me,
just giving me a horse.

509
00:32:46,326 --> 00:32:50,204
I'll be waiting for you
after supper out by the bell.

510
00:32:50,086 --> 00:32:52,087
I won't go.

511
00:32:53,367 --> 00:32:55,118
I won't!

512
00:33:01,127 --> 00:33:04,089
Listen to this for poppycock.

513
00:33:04,007 --> 00:33:06,969
"And the benefits
to be derived...

514
00:33:06,888 --> 00:33:10,849
"by the small ranchers
from the new railroad...

515
00:33:10,728 --> 00:33:14,773
"are too numerous
to need recounting here."

516
00:33:14,649 --> 00:33:16,192
"Small ranchers."

517
00:33:16,170 --> 00:33:18,796
Ignorant, nasty,
spoiling the open range...

518
00:33:18,729 --> 00:33:20,355
with their measly fences.

519
00:33:20,330 --> 00:33:23,291
And say, Jesse.
I should have told you before.

520
00:33:23,210 --> 00:33:25,171
Them surveyors had the gall...

521
00:33:25,130 --> 00:33:27,590
to come traipsing
over Spanish Bit...

522
00:33:27,531 --> 00:33:30,366
with them infernal
spyglasses of theirs.

523
00:33:30,291 --> 00:33:32,876
I almost fired
that new foreman Ken...

524
00:33:32,810 --> 00:33:34,645
for letting them on the place.

525
00:33:35,851 --> 00:33:37,978
Shouldn't have
done that, Senator.

526
00:33:37,932 --> 00:33:39,224
Why not?

527
00:33:39,212 --> 00:33:41,005
Because it wasn't Ken
who let them on the place.

528
00:33:40,972 --> 00:33:42,931
Nobody else would
have had the nerve.

529
00:33:42,893 --> 00:33:45,436
I was the one that told them
they could do it.

530
00:33:45,373 --> 00:33:48,125
- Have you gone plumb crazy?
- I don't think so.

531
00:33:48,052 --> 00:33:50,054
I thought it might be
a good idea to cooperate...

532
00:33:50,013 --> 00:33:52,473
and have the tracks where
they'd do the most good.

533
00:33:52,413 --> 00:33:54,790
Good? What do you mean good?

534
00:33:54,734 --> 00:33:56,235
It's getting rather cool,
don't you think?

535
00:33:56,253 --> 00:33:58,213
For one thing...

536
00:33:58,173 --> 00:34:00,633
the railroad will bring
new people, a school.

537
00:34:00,574 --> 00:34:02,743
Paradise Flats will become
a real town instead of...

538
00:34:02,694 --> 00:34:04,946
And that same railway
will ship...

539
00:34:04,894 --> 00:34:08,355
a lot of emigrants
from up north down here...

540
00:34:08,256 --> 00:34:11,925
and they'll start in voting
and putting in taxes.

541
00:34:11,816 --> 00:34:14,067
It's your ranch.

542
00:34:14,016 --> 00:34:16,684
I was just trying to be helpful.

543
00:34:20,136 --> 00:34:23,222
Spanish Bit's going to
belong to you someday...

544
00:34:23,136 --> 00:34:24,805
you and Lewt.

545
00:34:24,777 --> 00:34:26,527
So I don't see why you don't...

546
00:34:26,497 --> 00:34:28,457
Senator, I know
you mean well for me.

547
00:34:28,418 --> 00:34:30,377
You've always been
generous to us.

548
00:34:30,338 --> 00:34:32,798
Maybe Lewt and I would be closer
to what you wanted us to be...

549
00:34:32,737 --> 00:34:34,239
if you hadn't been so generous.

550
00:34:34,219 --> 00:34:36,678
What's wrong with Lewt?

551
00:34:36,618 --> 00:34:38,244
Nothing at all
that you'd object to.

552
00:34:38,219 --> 00:34:40,304
That's not the point.
I'm the one who's the maverick.

553
00:34:40,259 --> 00:34:43,594
I don't know
what you're talking about.

554
00:34:43,499 --> 00:34:46,543
I'd like one McCanles to give
something to this state...

555
00:34:46,459 --> 00:34:48,085
and not just take from it.

556
00:34:50,619 --> 00:34:52,871
Good night, sir.

557
00:34:58,621 --> 00:35:00,955
Your son, ma'am?

558
00:35:02,301 --> 00:35:04,135
Yes, Senator.

559
00:35:08,702 --> 00:35:10,662
Who's there?

560
00:35:10,621 --> 00:35:13,081
Is that you, Jesse?

561
00:35:13,022 --> 00:35:17,275
Hello, Pearl. Nice night.
Want to take a little walk?

562
00:35:18,624 --> 00:35:20,750
It's kind of late.
I think I'd better go...

563
00:35:20,704 --> 00:35:22,663
Where were you going when l...

564
00:35:22,623 --> 00:35:27,669
Got to get me
somebody to love

565
00:35:27,504 --> 00:35:29,547
I...

566
00:35:29,504 --> 00:35:31,130
I guess that's Lewt.

567
00:35:31,105 --> 00:35:32,731
Certainly is Lewt.
He's the best serenader...

568
00:35:32,704 --> 00:35:34,331
this side of the Rio Grande.

569
00:35:34,305 --> 00:35:37,599
I don't care if he is.
Him and his old guitar.

570
00:35:37,506 --> 00:35:40,425
Just because he gave me a horse.

571
00:35:40,346 --> 00:35:43,765
I know why, too.
He can't fool me none.

572
00:35:43,666 --> 00:35:46,043
That's a horse
on Lewt, isn't it?

573
00:35:45,987 --> 00:35:48,530
I didn't really
want to meet him.

574
00:35:48,466 --> 00:35:50,426
Honest, I didn't.

575
00:35:50,386 --> 00:35:53,348
It was just that
I was kind of lonesome and...

576
00:35:53,266 --> 00:35:54,726
I know.

577
00:35:54,707 --> 00:35:58,418
Do you still want me
to take that walk with you?

578
00:35:59,668 --> 00:36:01,461
I don't know why not.

579
00:36:01,428 --> 00:36:04,430
Lewt can supply the charming
musical background.

580
00:36:06,829 --> 00:36:12,666
Got to get me
somebody to love

581
00:36:12,468 --> 00:36:14,470
I'll be...

582
00:36:36,512 --> 00:36:37,929
Thanks, Lewt.

583
00:36:37,911 --> 00:36:40,538
You're a better wrangler
than all of them.

584
00:36:40,471 --> 00:36:42,432
Sid, see that chestnut
over there?

585
00:36:42,392 --> 00:36:44,352
She looks lame.
Take her out to pasture.

586
00:36:44,312 --> 00:36:45,564
Sure.

587
00:36:45,553 --> 00:36:47,054
It's hotter than a stove lid.

588
00:36:47,032 --> 00:36:49,993
Sure wish we was over
at the sump right now.

589
00:36:49,913 --> 00:36:52,207
And somebody else figures
the same way, I reckon.

590
00:36:52,154 --> 00:36:53,988
Looks like she's heading
for a cool-off.

591
00:36:57,914 --> 00:37:00,165
- I'll see you later.
- Where are you going, boss?

592
00:37:00,114 --> 00:37:03,825
- I got business.
- That lucky stiff.

593
00:37:05,115 --> 00:37:06,949
I wish I was a McCanles.

594
00:37:27,117 --> 00:37:28,868
Good afternoon.

595
00:37:29,918 --> 00:37:32,294
How's that water?
As cool as it looks?

596
00:37:32,238 --> 00:37:33,697
You go away from here.

597
00:37:33,718 --> 00:37:35,970
- Care for a swimming lesson?
- No.

598
00:37:35,919 --> 00:37:38,254
What if I just stay around,
keep you company?

599
00:37:38,198 --> 00:37:39,325
Don't you dare.

600
00:37:39,319 --> 00:37:41,612
I'm sorry, honey.
I can't hear a word you say.

601
00:37:41,519 --> 00:37:42,854
Move over.

602
00:37:42,840 --> 00:37:44,340
You can't come in here.

603
00:37:44,319 --> 00:37:46,278
Just act like I'm not even here.

604
00:37:47,559 --> 00:37:49,393
Act like we never even met.

605
00:38:04,722 --> 00:38:06,473
You disappointed?

606
00:38:10,522 --> 00:38:13,315
If you ain't the lowest,
dirtiest, meanest...

607
00:38:13,242 --> 00:38:15,201
Come on out.
I ain't stopping you.

608
00:38:15,162 --> 00:38:16,747
I can't, with you there.

609
00:38:16,724 --> 00:38:20,226
Wait till it's plumb dark,
for all I care.

610
00:38:25,404 --> 00:38:27,531
Let go! Let me down!

611
00:38:27,484 --> 00:38:29,945
Making me late for supper
just to be mean!

612
00:38:29,885 --> 00:38:31,344
What will your ma think?

613
00:38:31,324 --> 00:38:33,118
If you hadn't been so doggone
scared I'd see something...

614
00:38:33,085 --> 00:38:35,962
you'd have been home
a long time ago.

615
00:38:35,885 --> 00:38:38,220
Little tiger cat.

616
00:38:42,126 --> 00:38:45,128
Evening, Pearl.
Have a good swim?

617
00:38:46,286 --> 00:38:47,704
Let me through!

618
00:38:52,046 --> 00:38:53,881
Am I too late for supper?

619
00:38:53,847 --> 00:38:56,098
I mean, is everybody finished?

620
00:38:56,047 --> 00:38:58,007
Mrs. McCanles say anything?

621
00:38:57,968 --> 00:39:01,429
Yes, ma'am.
She said, "Where's Miss Pearl?"

622
00:39:01,328 --> 00:39:03,287
And I said, "I don't know,
Mrs. McCanles."

623
00:39:03,249 --> 00:39:05,208
And she said,
"Where's Mr. Lewton?"

624
00:39:05,169 --> 00:39:07,629
And I said,
"I don't know, ma'am."

625
00:39:07,569 --> 00:39:09,028
And she said, "Well..."

626
00:39:09,009 --> 00:39:11,218
Pearl, dearest.

627
00:39:11,169 --> 00:39:12,879
I was so worried about you.

628
00:39:12,850 --> 00:39:14,308
Sorry, ma'am.

629
00:39:14,289 --> 00:39:16,249
What happened?

630
00:39:16,210 --> 00:39:17,669
I went riding.

631
00:39:17,650 --> 00:39:19,610
With Lewton?

632
00:39:19,570 --> 00:39:21,988
Vashti, get Miss Pearl
some supper.

633
00:39:21,930 --> 00:39:23,265
Yes, ma'am.

634
00:39:23,251 --> 00:39:24,876
The Senator's
got rules about supper.

635
00:39:24,851 --> 00:39:26,810
He says to me,
"Don't you ever..."

636
00:39:26,771 --> 00:39:28,523
- Vashti.
- Yes, ma'am.

637
00:39:28,491 --> 00:39:31,160
Did you go riding with Lewton?

638
00:39:31,092 --> 00:39:32,468
No, ma'am...

639
00:39:32,452 --> 00:39:34,411
I didn't go riding with Lewton.

640
00:39:34,372 --> 00:39:36,831
He wasn't here
for supper either.

641
00:39:36,772 --> 00:39:38,232
He's coming.

642
00:39:38,213 --> 00:39:40,172
But he wasn't with you?

643
00:39:40,132 --> 00:39:43,092
We just happened to meet up.

644
00:39:43,012 --> 00:39:46,180
I see.
But why is your hair wet?

645
00:39:49,253 --> 00:39:51,713
I was down to the sump.

646
00:39:51,654 --> 00:39:53,614
You went in swimming?

647
00:39:53,574 --> 00:39:55,533
Yes, ma'am.

648
00:39:55,494 --> 00:39:56,995
With Lewton?

649
00:39:58,374 --> 00:39:59,875
No, ma'am.

650
00:40:00,934 --> 00:40:03,228
I didn't, ma'am.
Honest, I didn't.

651
00:40:03,175 --> 00:40:05,134
I didn't, ma'am.

652
00:40:05,095 --> 00:40:07,554
All right, Pearl. L...

653
00:40:08,615 --> 00:40:09,783
Evening, ma.

654
00:40:09,776 --> 00:40:11,359
Good evening, Lewton.

655
00:40:11,336 --> 00:40:15,131
Sorry to be late.
We were down to the sump.

656
00:40:18,056 --> 00:40:22,017
I think I'll take a ride
over to El Paso tomorrow...

657
00:40:21,897 --> 00:40:24,357
and get me a little fun
and relaxation.

658
00:40:24,297 --> 00:40:26,256
Anything I can bring you, ma?

659
00:40:26,217 --> 00:40:27,843
No, thank you.

660
00:40:27,817 --> 00:40:30,068
Pearl, I think
I'll try to get you one...

661
00:40:30,017 --> 00:40:31,977
of them newfangled
bathing suits.

662
00:40:31,938 --> 00:40:36,566
She swims real well, ma.
Where'd you learn?

663
00:40:36,418 --> 00:40:37,878
Oh, my dear!

664
00:40:39,619 --> 00:40:41,579
You... you varmint!

665
00:40:41,540 --> 00:40:44,083
What you getting
your bristles up about?

666
00:40:48,739 --> 00:40:49,907
Giddy!

667
00:40:56,942 --> 00:40:58,859
Miss Pearl, wake up.

668
00:40:58,821 --> 00:41:00,780
What is it?

669
00:41:00,741 --> 00:41:02,701
What's the matter?

670
00:41:02,662 --> 00:41:04,121
Well...

671
00:41:04,102 --> 00:41:05,561
What time is it?

672
00:41:05,542 --> 00:41:07,501
It must have been about 9:00...

673
00:41:07,462 --> 00:41:09,923
when Mrs. McCanles
says to me, "Vashti...

674
00:41:09,862 --> 00:41:13,322
"when Mr. Jubal Crabby
gets here..."

675
00:41:13,222 --> 00:41:16,891
What is it? Who's Mr. Crabby?

676
00:41:16,782 --> 00:41:19,034
Why did you wake me up?

677
00:41:18,984 --> 00:41:20,443
I almost forgot.

678
00:41:20,424 --> 00:41:24,385
Mrs. McCanles wants to see you
up in the sitting room.

679
00:41:24,265 --> 00:41:26,808
Maybe you better hurry.
She's been a-waiting.

680
00:41:26,744 --> 00:41:28,538
I didn't know where you was...

681
00:41:28,505 --> 00:41:30,839
so I said,
"I'll go see Mr. Lewton."

682
00:41:30,785 --> 00:41:32,244
And he said...

683
00:41:32,224 --> 00:41:34,310
Why are you so slow?

684
00:41:34,266 --> 00:41:35,891
I don't rightly know...

685
00:41:35,865 --> 00:41:39,117
exceptin' I always have
so much to remember.

686
00:41:40,546 --> 00:41:42,839
This is the child, Jubal.

687
00:41:42,787 --> 00:41:45,914
Of course, she isn't dressed
quite properly, but...

688
00:41:45,826 --> 00:41:47,286
Close the door, Pearl.

689
00:41:47,267 --> 00:41:49,226
This is Mr. Crabby.

690
00:41:49,187 --> 00:41:51,146
We have no minister
in these parts, but...

691
00:41:51,107 --> 00:41:54,568
A man doesn't have to wear
the cloth to be a sinkiller.

692
00:41:54,467 --> 00:41:56,928
I know that.
That's why I was so anxious...

693
00:41:56,867 --> 00:41:58,827
to have you talk to the child.

694
00:41:58,788 --> 00:42:00,288
Come here, girl.

695
00:42:03,588 --> 00:42:06,548
You call her a child?

696
00:42:06,469 --> 00:42:07,929
Under that heathen blanket...

697
00:42:07,909 --> 00:42:09,869
there's
a full-blossomed woman...

698
00:42:09,829 --> 00:42:12,332
built by the devil
to drive men crazy!

699
00:42:13,669 --> 00:42:15,129
You mustn't frighten her.

700
00:42:15,110 --> 00:42:17,778
I'm sure she only needs
a little guidance.

701
00:42:17,710 --> 00:42:20,462
Guidance she needs,
and guidance she'll get...

702
00:42:20,390 --> 00:42:22,350
or I ain't been the sinkiller...

703
00:42:22,309 --> 00:42:24,770
from here to El Paso
for thirty years.

704
00:42:24,711 --> 00:42:26,712
Sit down, girl.

705
00:42:29,031 --> 00:42:31,491
You could be a woman of sin
or a woman of God.

706
00:42:31,431 --> 00:42:33,391
Which is it to be?

707
00:42:33,352 --> 00:42:35,311
I want to be a good girl.

708
00:42:35,272 --> 00:42:37,149
Then remember that the devil's
always able to hog-tie you.

709
00:42:37,112 --> 00:42:39,072
Sometimes he comes
ghosting over the plains...

710
00:42:39,032 --> 00:42:40,992
in the shape
of a sneaking rustler...

711
00:42:40,952 --> 00:42:43,413
and sometimes... begging
your pardon, Laura Belle...

712
00:42:43,353 --> 00:42:44,812
he stakes out the home...

713
00:42:44,792 --> 00:42:46,753
to the worthy
and the God-fearing.

714
00:42:46,713 --> 00:42:49,674
You're curved
in the flesh of temptation.

715
00:42:49,594 --> 00:42:52,054
Resisting is gonna be
a darn sight harder for you...

716
00:42:51,994 --> 00:42:53,953
than for females protected
by the shape of sows.

717
00:42:53,914 --> 00:42:56,375
Yes, sirree, bob, you've got to
sweeten yourself with prayer.

718
00:42:56,314 --> 00:42:57,773
Pray till you sweat...

719
00:42:57,754 --> 00:42:59,713
and you'll save yourself
eternal hellfire.

720
00:42:59,674 --> 00:43:02,385
- Do you understand me, girl?
- Yes, sir.

721
00:43:02,315 --> 00:43:04,024
Then on your knees.

722
00:43:03,995 --> 00:43:06,955
Now I'm gonna start you
toward salvation.

723
00:43:06,875 --> 00:43:09,334
O Lord, look upon this,
thy creature.

724
00:43:09,275 --> 00:43:11,736
She's a weak vessel
and a pauper, as thou knowest.

725
00:43:11,676 --> 00:43:13,843
But she wants to be
thy handmaiden.

726
00:43:13,797 --> 00:43:16,048
Give her the horse sense
not to go wandering off...

727
00:43:15,997 --> 00:43:18,333
in the tulies
with worthless cowpokes.

728
00:43:18,277 --> 00:43:19,611
Amen.

729
00:43:22,797 --> 00:43:24,674
Rise, girl.

730
00:43:24,637 --> 00:43:26,973
Here. I want you to take this.

731
00:43:26,917 --> 00:43:29,836
It's a hallowed medal,
and a good one.

732
00:43:29,758 --> 00:43:31,884
I took it off
a thieving card sharper...

733
00:43:31,838 --> 00:43:33,297
but first I shrived him...

734
00:43:33,278 --> 00:43:35,196
and sent him
to the pearly gates...

735
00:43:35,159 --> 00:43:38,120
as nice and pretty as any from
his own faith could have done.

736
00:43:38,039 --> 00:43:40,000
You wear it, girl.

737
00:43:39,959 --> 00:43:41,919
Thank you, sir.

738
00:43:41,879 --> 00:43:43,839
Part Indian, ain't you?

739
00:43:43,799 --> 00:43:46,260
Those ancestors of yours
will be spinning like tops...

740
00:43:46,200 --> 00:43:48,159
when they know you got this on.

741
00:43:48,120 --> 00:43:50,079
Just the same, it'll keep you...

742
00:43:50,040 --> 00:43:52,501
sweet and clean
as the first milking.

743
00:43:52,440 --> 00:43:53,899
Won't get you into heaven...

744
00:43:53,880 --> 00:43:56,340
but it will comfort you
on the way there.

745
00:43:56,280 --> 00:43:58,241
That is, if you use it right.

746
00:44:00,121 --> 00:44:02,082
Laura Belle, don't you think...

747
00:44:02,042 --> 00:44:04,002
we ought to be saying
a few words of prayer...

748
00:44:03,962 --> 00:44:05,922
for them worthless cowpokes?

749
00:44:05,882 --> 00:44:09,844
I got a feeling
they'll be needing...

750
00:44:09,722 --> 00:44:11,057
consolation.

751
00:44:13,562 --> 00:44:15,522
On your knees again, girl.

752
00:44:16,923 --> 00:44:19,883
O Lord, have mercy on all men,
young and old alike...

753
00:44:19,803 --> 00:44:23,764
who gaze upon this,
thy regained servant.

754
00:44:23,645 --> 00:44:25,104
Amen.

755
00:44:34,124 --> 00:44:36,085
Senator! Where's the Senator?

756
00:44:36,045 --> 00:44:37,629
What's up?

757
00:44:37,605 --> 00:44:39,941
- Senator McCanles!
- What's the stampede?

758
00:44:39,885 --> 00:44:42,013
There's a great big railway gang
down close to the east fence.

759
00:44:41,966 --> 00:44:43,425
How close?

760
00:44:43,406 --> 00:44:45,366
They say they're coming across
Spanish Bit line this afternoon.

761
00:44:45,327 --> 00:44:47,620
- What will we do?
- Get ahold of Lewt and Jesse.

762
00:44:47,567 --> 00:44:49,527
Lewt's not back from El Paso.

763
00:44:49,486 --> 00:44:52,947
Holleration.
I guess Jesse and me...

764
00:44:52,847 --> 00:44:54,807
can handle it all right.

765
00:44:54,768 --> 00:44:57,228
- Sid.
- Yes, Senator?

766
00:44:57,168 --> 00:44:59,127
Listen carefully now.

767
00:44:59,088 --> 00:45:02,548
Sound every bell
from here to Blue Hills ranch.

768
00:45:02,448 --> 00:45:05,909
I want every wrangler,
every cowhand...

769
00:45:05,809 --> 00:45:08,769
every man and boy
on Spanish Bit...

770
00:45:08,690 --> 00:45:12,693
down there at the east fence,
and I want them there fast.

771
00:45:12,569 --> 00:45:14,154
- Yes, sir.
- And Sid.

772
00:45:14,130 --> 00:45:16,923
- Yes, sir?
- I want them there armed.

773
00:45:16,850 --> 00:45:18,392
You betcha.

774
00:46:11,616 --> 00:46:13,493
I don't like this, Mr. Langford.

775
00:46:13,417 --> 00:46:15,418
It's your railroad,
and it's your headache...

776
00:46:15,337 --> 00:46:17,671
but I still don't like it.

777
00:46:17,617 --> 00:46:19,202
What do you mean,
you don't like it?

778
00:46:19,178 --> 00:46:21,137
You told me we were legally
in the clear, didn't you?

779
00:46:21,098 --> 00:46:23,557
Yeah, and I know you asked
the army for help, too.

780
00:46:23,497 --> 00:46:26,500
And I hope they don't come.
And I hope we don't need them.

781
00:46:26,378 --> 00:46:27,795
What do you mean?

782
00:46:27,778 --> 00:46:30,738
I mean Jackson McCanles
don't scare so easy.

783
00:46:30,658 --> 00:46:34,744
We roamed the plains together.
We fought at Vicksburg together.

784
00:46:34,618 --> 00:46:36,953
And if he gives up
in this fight...

785
00:46:36,898 --> 00:46:39,275
he ain't the man
I've known for fifty years.

786
00:46:39,220 --> 00:46:41,263
I wish you wouldn't
try to ride, father.

787
00:46:41,220 --> 00:46:43,179
You think I'm going
to sit in this house...

788
00:46:43,140 --> 00:46:45,933
like some old woman?
Lift me on that horse.

789
00:46:45,860 --> 00:46:48,528
If they want war,
they can have it.

790
00:46:50,461 --> 00:46:52,462
- Ken.
- Yes, sir?

791
00:46:52,420 --> 00:46:54,130
Strap me on here.

792
00:46:56,621 --> 00:46:58,580
Come on.

793
00:47:46,747 --> 00:47:50,375
I aim to defend
Spanish Bit with lead.

794
00:47:50,268 --> 00:47:55,062
If there's any yellow-bellies
among you, get out now.

795
00:47:57,229 --> 00:47:59,230
Are you with me?

796
00:48:01,508 --> 00:48:03,759
All right, then.
Spread out in a line...

797
00:48:03,708 --> 00:48:06,669
from the west marker
to Pinto Point.

798
00:48:06,589 --> 00:48:09,090
Come on!

799
00:49:33,359 --> 00:49:36,820
Kind of thought he wouldn't
take this lying down.

800
00:49:36,719 --> 00:49:39,220
Looks like they mean business.

801
00:49:45,840 --> 00:49:47,257
Smoot!

802
00:49:52,561 --> 00:49:55,605
Lem Smoot, I thought you had
more sense than this.

803
00:49:55,522 --> 00:49:58,732
Yeah? Since when did you
ever know me to dodge a fight?

804
00:49:58,642 --> 00:50:00,226
You know I'm lawyer
for the railroad...

805
00:50:00,201 --> 00:50:03,078
Never mind that stuff.
Who's the dude?

806
00:50:03,002 --> 00:50:05,755
Langford is the high
mucky-muck on the railway.

807
00:50:05,683 --> 00:50:08,227
Heard a lot about you, Senator.
Glad to make your acquaintance.

808
00:50:08,163 --> 00:50:11,165
Can't say the same,
thank you kindly.

809
00:50:11,043 --> 00:50:13,253
You better tell those
hired thieves of yours...

810
00:50:13,203 --> 00:50:14,996
to pick up their tools...

811
00:50:14,964 --> 00:50:17,841
and fast, if you know
what's good for you.

812
00:50:17,763 --> 00:50:19,222
We have the law on our side.

813
00:50:19,203 --> 00:50:21,205
If you had come into court
when I asked you to...

814
00:50:21,124 --> 00:50:22,750
this land might not have been...

815
00:50:22,724 --> 00:50:25,726
Never mind
that fancy legal talk.

816
00:50:25,605 --> 00:50:28,524
There's my law right there.

817
00:50:32,806 --> 00:50:35,307
Have you a copy
of the writ with you, Smoot?

818
00:50:35,205 --> 00:50:36,707
What's the sense of...

819
00:50:36,646 --> 00:50:38,480
All right. Are you our lawyer,
or aren't you?

820
00:50:38,406 --> 00:50:41,283
- Now read it to him.
- Save your breath.

821
00:50:41,206 --> 00:50:44,458
"From the people of
the sovereign state of Texas...

822
00:50:44,326 --> 00:50:46,328
"to Jackson Tilt McCanles,
greetings."

823
00:50:46,247 --> 00:50:48,373
"Greetings." Ain't that nice?

824
00:50:48,328 --> 00:50:49,786
Jackson.

825
00:50:49,767 --> 00:50:52,103
You and I fought to build
this state of Texas...

826
00:50:52,008 --> 00:50:54,468
and I aim to see these men
perform their duties...

827
00:50:54,408 --> 00:50:56,368
peacefully and as authorized.

828
00:50:56,328 --> 00:50:58,330
Is that so?

829
00:50:58,248 --> 00:51:01,918
I'm gonna shoot any trespasser
that comes on my property.

830
00:51:01,769 --> 00:51:05,229
If you don't like that,
you can lump it...

831
00:51:05,129 --> 00:51:06,630
you and the state of Texas.

832
00:51:06,569 --> 00:51:09,404
Just a minute.
May I speak to you privately?

833
00:51:09,289 --> 00:51:13,250
Say what you got to say
right here and now.

834
00:51:13,130 --> 00:51:14,631
I'm sorry, father...

835
00:51:14,571 --> 00:51:16,572
but I'm afraid
you're in the wrong.

836
00:51:16,490 --> 00:51:18,616
I ain't aiming
to let you settle that.

837
00:51:18,570 --> 00:51:20,280
You mean to shoot down
unarmed men?

838
00:51:20,251 --> 00:51:23,795
Just like they was rattlesnakes
if they cross this line.

839
00:51:23,692 --> 00:51:25,609
In that case, Senator...

840
00:51:33,292 --> 00:51:35,293
Get me a pair of wire cutters.

841
00:51:35,213 --> 00:51:36,339
Ferguson.

842
00:51:36,334 --> 00:51:38,710
So that's where you stand.

843
00:51:38,653 --> 00:51:40,112
Think I'd rather be
on the side...

844
00:51:40,093 --> 00:51:41,970
of the victims
than of the murderers.

845
00:51:46,253 --> 00:51:48,214
Jesse, I'm warning you.

846
00:51:48,174 --> 00:51:50,634
We're going to fire
on those coolies...

847
00:51:50,574 --> 00:51:53,701
the moment you cut those wires.

848
00:51:53,614 --> 00:51:55,574
Their blood will be
on your hands.

849
00:52:03,655 --> 00:52:08,283
Jesse, I'm asking you
for the last time.

850
00:52:16,457 --> 00:52:18,458
Column left. Ho!

851
00:52:22,418 --> 00:52:24,252
Thank God.

852
00:52:35,179 --> 00:52:37,180
Column left. Ho!

853
00:52:54,502 --> 00:52:57,379
Right front into lines. Ho!

854
00:53:36,546 --> 00:53:39,507
I once fought for that flag.

855
00:53:39,426 --> 00:53:41,428
I'll not fire on it.

856
00:53:48,067 --> 00:53:51,528
Sid, tell those men
to get back to their work.

857
00:53:51,429 --> 00:53:52,888
Yes, sir.

858
00:53:52,868 --> 00:53:54,328
Father, l...

859
00:53:54,309 --> 00:53:56,268
Get out of my sight...

860
00:53:56,229 --> 00:54:00,315
and stay away from Spanish Bit
as long as I live.

861
00:54:02,845 --> 00:54:05,181
Whoa, General!
Hey! Whoa, boy!

862
00:54:09,007 --> 00:54:13,010
Get me out of here!
Hey, get me out of here!

863
00:54:12,887 --> 00:54:15,515
Get me out of this!

864
00:54:21,050 --> 00:54:22,885
Unbuckle him!

865
00:54:25,851 --> 00:54:28,312
Are you all right, father?

866
00:54:28,252 --> 00:54:31,212
Leave me be, you Judas.

867
00:54:31,133 --> 00:54:33,094
Here.

868
00:54:40,735 --> 00:54:43,196
Fours left, column left.

869
00:54:43,137 --> 00:54:45,598
Gallop. Ho!

870
00:55:40,192 --> 00:55:41,693
Hiya.

871
00:55:55,077 --> 00:55:57,037
Afternoon, Mr. Lewton.

872
00:55:56,997 --> 00:55:58,958
Where the devil is everybody?
The place is deserted.

873
00:55:58,919 --> 00:56:00,378
I don't rightly know...

874
00:56:00,359 --> 00:56:02,318
exceptin' that
the Senator went riding.

875
00:56:02,279 --> 00:56:03,696
The senator went riding?

876
00:56:03,639 --> 00:56:05,474
You must be
going out of your mind.

877
00:56:05,399 --> 00:56:08,527
No, sir. He went riding
with lots and lots of other men.

878
00:56:08,442 --> 00:56:11,445
And I heard they're having
a kind of a meeting.

879
00:56:11,323 --> 00:56:12,824
What kind of a meeting?

880
00:56:12,763 --> 00:56:16,224
I don't rightly know,
but I said to Mrs. McCanles...

881
00:56:16,124 --> 00:56:18,125
"Mrs. McCanles, where are
all those men going?"

882
00:56:18,043 --> 00:56:19,669
And she said...

883
00:56:19,645 --> 00:56:21,480
Never mind.

884
00:56:21,405 --> 00:56:22,906
She did say...

885
00:56:22,845 --> 00:56:25,347
"Vashti, go right on
about your business.

886
00:56:25,246 --> 00:56:27,457
"Right on about your business."

887
00:58:07,556 --> 00:58:10,349
I guess this means
good-bye for a while.

888
00:58:10,277 --> 00:58:11,737
Now, don't you cry.

889
00:58:11,717 --> 00:58:13,343
I'll be back before long...

890
00:58:13,317 --> 00:58:16,111
and he'll get over it
when the railroad comes through.

891
00:58:16,038 --> 00:58:18,498
I always knew you'd
have to leave someday...

892
00:58:18,439 --> 00:58:21,400
but now that it's come,
I just can't bear it.

893
00:58:21,320 --> 00:58:23,279
It's not as bad as all that.

894
00:58:23,240 --> 00:58:26,201
I'll get a place in Austin.
You can come visit me.

895
00:58:26,121 --> 00:58:28,081
If you're a good girl,
I might even take you...

896
00:58:28,042 --> 00:58:30,002
on a little trip to New Orleans.

897
00:58:29,962 --> 00:58:31,922
No. He'd never forgive me.

898
00:58:31,883 --> 00:58:35,344
I'll never see you again. Never.

899
00:58:35,244 --> 00:58:37,203
I know it.

900
00:58:37,164 --> 00:58:41,126
He said he'd shoot you
if you ever step foot on...

901
00:58:41,005 --> 00:58:43,675
One McCanles can be
just as tough as another.

902
00:58:44,605 --> 00:58:48,317
Mrs. McCanles, come in here!

903
00:58:48,207 --> 00:58:50,376
You better go to him now.

904
00:58:52,529 --> 00:58:54,990
But you won't go yet awhile?

905
00:58:54,929 --> 00:58:57,890
No. I'll just pack my things
and say good-bye to Pearl.

906
00:59:25,778 --> 00:59:27,613
Are you there?

907
00:59:32,339 --> 00:59:35,133
Jesse, go away, please.

908
00:59:35,061 --> 00:59:37,189
What you scared of,
Pearl, honey?

909
00:59:37,142 --> 00:59:39,269
Come on in.

910
00:59:45,304 --> 00:59:47,555
Thanks for knocking.

911
00:59:50,585 --> 00:59:52,545
I didn't used to think...

912
00:59:52,506 --> 00:59:55,383
there was much to all those
fancy manners of yours...

913
00:59:55,305 --> 00:59:57,224
but I guess I was wrong.

914
01:00:02,989 --> 01:00:04,908
Jesse, I...

915
01:00:06,190 --> 01:00:08,358
Forgive me for intruding, Pearl.

916
01:00:10,351 --> 01:00:12,019
You, too, Lewt.

917
01:00:16,912 --> 01:00:18,414
Good-bye, Pearl.

918
01:00:22,995 --> 01:00:25,456
Wait a minute, please!

919
01:00:25,395 --> 01:00:26,855
I didn't mean to...

920
01:00:26,835 --> 01:00:28,796
It's all right.
I understand perfectly.

921
01:00:28,757 --> 01:00:30,925
No, you don't.

922
01:00:32,277 --> 01:00:35,739
- Where are you going?
- I'm going to Austin.

923
01:00:35,638 --> 01:00:38,474
You gonna be gone long?

924
01:00:39,799 --> 01:00:41,634
Quite long, I'm afraid.

925
01:00:43,321 --> 01:00:45,114
It isn't because of...

926
01:00:45,082 --> 01:00:47,208
No. Bless your heart.

927
01:00:47,162 --> 01:00:52,083
I'm leaving by request...
the Senator's request.

928
01:00:54,685 --> 01:00:56,227
Going away, Jesse?

929
01:00:56,203 --> 01:00:59,831
Uh-huh. Your dream's come true.
I'm going away.

930
01:00:59,725 --> 01:01:02,102
It's gonna seem
kind of lonely around here...

931
01:01:02,045 --> 01:01:04,673
without the judge,
ain't it, Pearl?

932
01:01:04,607 --> 01:01:05,984
Yes, it is.

933
01:01:05,967 --> 01:01:07,427
Don't see how we'll know...

934
01:01:07,407 --> 01:01:10,452
when we're doing right
and when we're doing wrong.

935
01:01:10,368 --> 01:01:12,662
You surprise me.
First time I knew...

936
01:01:12,609 --> 01:01:14,944
you were interested in ethics.

937
01:01:17,891 --> 01:01:20,351
I'm sure you folks
will excuse me.

938
01:01:20,291 --> 01:01:23,753
You must have a lot of things
you want to talk over.

939
01:01:23,652 --> 01:01:27,780
The nights are long, oh, so long

940
01:01:27,654 --> 01:01:30,615
It is going to be
lonesome without you.

941
01:01:30,535 --> 01:01:32,996
I just don't know
how I can stand it.

942
01:01:32,935 --> 01:01:35,187
You seem to be doing all right.

943
01:01:37,096 --> 01:01:40,016
I'm sorry. That was mean of me.

944
01:01:41,257 --> 01:01:42,717
I couldn't help it.

945
01:01:42,698 --> 01:01:45,158
You just can't go away
believing...

946
01:01:45,098 --> 01:01:47,224
I tried hard. Honest, I did.

947
01:01:47,179 --> 01:01:48,930
I know.

948
01:01:48,859 --> 01:01:50,861
Lewt's hard to resist.

949
01:01:50,781 --> 01:01:52,782
No! I hate him!

950
01:01:52,701 --> 01:01:55,371
I know what you're thinking.

951
01:01:57,182 --> 01:02:02,145
I guess I'm just...
trash, like my ma.

952
01:02:01,983 --> 01:02:03,610
You mustn't believe that.

953
01:02:03,584 --> 01:02:05,586
It was Lewt's fault.
You needed some help.

954
01:02:05,505 --> 01:02:08,173
I did. I needed you to help me.

955
01:02:12,066 --> 01:02:14,067
I might as well say it.

956
01:02:13,987 --> 01:02:16,489
I loved you.
Somehow you touched me.

957
01:02:16,387 --> 01:02:18,889
You... love me?

958
01:02:18,788 --> 01:02:21,792
I thought of what you'd be like
when you grew up a little.

959
01:02:23,589 --> 01:02:25,216
I didn't know.

960
01:02:25,190 --> 01:02:27,025
Why didn't you tell me?

961
01:02:26,950 --> 01:02:28,785
I didn't think it would
be fair to tell you.

962
01:02:28,711 --> 01:02:30,338
I was a fool.

963
01:02:33,032 --> 01:02:35,159
I came to your room
to say good-bye...

964
01:02:35,113 --> 01:02:39,075
to tell you that someday
I'd be back for you...

965
01:02:38,954 --> 01:02:41,624
that I'd think about you
and that I'd write...

966
01:02:49,477 --> 01:02:51,437
I'll write to you.

967
01:02:51,397 --> 01:02:54,025
You will?

968
01:02:53,958 --> 01:02:57,753
If you need me, I'll come back,
Senator or no Senator.

969
01:02:57,639 --> 01:03:00,100
And you'll forget about...

970
01:03:00,040 --> 01:03:03,043
about tonight, won't you?

971
01:03:04,361 --> 01:03:06,321
You'll forget it?

972
01:03:06,283 --> 01:03:08,910
No, I don't think I'll forget.

973
01:03:08,842 --> 01:03:11,344
I don't think
I'll ever be able to.

974
01:03:13,324 --> 01:03:15,951
I shouldn't have told you
the way I felt.

975
01:03:15,884 --> 01:03:17,552
It wasn't fair.

976
01:03:20,525 --> 01:03:24,362
There I go again,
trying to be fair.

977
01:03:31,248 --> 01:03:32,751
Trash.

978
01:03:40,212 --> 01:03:42,338
I hear you turned out to be...

979
01:03:42,292 --> 01:03:45,544
a prize yellow dog
down at the fence line.

980
01:03:49,894 --> 01:03:52,897
I should have done that
to you years ago.

981
01:04:05,258 --> 01:04:09,220
Nights are long, oh, so long

982
01:04:09,100 --> 01:04:13,229
On the prairie

983
01:04:13,101 --> 01:04:19,940
Got to get me somebody to love

984
01:04:26,865 --> 01:04:29,033
The dirty skunk!

985
01:05:07,156 --> 01:05:09,617
All right, Jesse.

986
01:05:09,557 --> 01:05:12,518
You said you'd never forget.

987
01:05:36,445 --> 01:05:38,280
This the other one
you meant, Lewt?

988
01:05:44,848 --> 01:05:47,101
You don't like this,
but you're gonna get it...

989
01:05:47,009 --> 01:05:49,260
right over the head
if you don't settle down.

990
01:05:49,209 --> 01:05:51,628
What's the matter?
You having trouble?

991
01:05:53,170 --> 01:05:54,505
Back, you killer! Back!

992
01:05:57,612 --> 01:05:59,154
Here, Ed.

993
01:06:04,054 --> 01:06:06,431
Don't pick up that halter!
He'll charge you!

994
01:06:06,374 --> 01:06:08,585
You're scared of him,
and he knows it.

995
01:06:08,534 --> 01:06:10,619
Never run from him.
Stand your ground.

996
01:06:12,575 --> 01:06:14,035
Come on, boy.

997
01:06:14,016 --> 01:06:16,643
I got a nice leather
bonnet for you.

998
01:06:19,298 --> 01:06:21,383
Easy, boy.

999
01:06:24,540 --> 01:06:25,540
Be careful.

1000
01:06:32,942 --> 01:06:35,651
- He's just plumb crazy!
- Don't you worry none about him.

1001
01:06:48,667 --> 01:06:50,502
Look out! Watch his feet!

1002
01:06:58,469 --> 01:07:00,763
He's got his ear.
Ear him down!

1003
01:07:00,709 --> 01:07:03,254
Dig 'em deep.

1004
01:07:03,190 --> 01:07:05,066
That'll stop him.

1005
01:07:25,276 --> 01:07:27,029
You got him.

1006
01:07:29,117 --> 01:07:31,119
Nobody could
have done it but you.

1007
01:07:31,038 --> 01:07:34,166
That's all there is to it.
Just don't let him bluff you.

1008
01:07:36,761 --> 01:07:39,722
You see, there ain't nothing
to handling stallions.

1009
01:07:39,641 --> 01:07:42,602
It just takes
a little know-how.

1010
01:07:42,521 --> 01:07:44,190
You sure got nerve.

1011
01:07:45,562 --> 01:07:47,230
Get away, Ed.

1012
01:07:48,283 --> 01:07:49,784
You're the boss.

1013
01:07:59,808 --> 01:08:00,934
What?

1014
01:08:00,927 --> 01:08:03,722
You don't have to stay
around here anymore, do you?

1015
01:08:03,648 --> 01:08:06,609
Don't never have to do nothing.

1016
01:08:06,528 --> 01:08:08,989
I stay around here
because I like it.

1017
01:08:08,929 --> 01:08:11,556
Bet you I can hit
that ding-dong straight off.

1018
01:08:11,490 --> 01:08:13,491
Who cares?

1019
01:08:15,171 --> 01:08:17,131
What's up?

1020
01:08:17,091 --> 01:08:20,052
Nothing. Just practicing.

1021
01:08:19,973 --> 01:08:21,933
Can you shoot?

1022
01:08:21,893 --> 01:08:23,853
Sure. It's easy.

1023
01:08:23,815 --> 01:08:26,775
That's what you said
about bareback riding.

1024
01:08:26,695 --> 01:08:28,654
All right, I'll show you.

1025
01:08:28,615 --> 01:08:31,075
Better not try it.
You might hit Ken...

1026
01:08:31,016 --> 01:08:32,851
or the mare, more likely.

1027
01:08:35,737 --> 01:08:39,198
Sure is doggone hot.

1028
01:08:39,098 --> 01:08:41,308
Sure is.

1029
01:08:41,259 --> 01:08:43,469
You know what I'd like to do?

1030
01:08:43,419 --> 01:08:44,879
What?

1031
01:08:44,860 --> 01:08:47,320
I'd like to take a swim.

1032
01:08:47,261 --> 01:08:49,220
You mean it?

1033
01:08:49,181 --> 01:08:51,642
Sure, I mean it.

1034
01:08:51,582 --> 01:08:53,875
Let's go to the sump.

1035
01:08:53,823 --> 01:08:56,157
I don't mind if I do.

1036
01:09:07,907 --> 01:09:09,867
Am I your girl?

1037
01:09:09,827 --> 01:09:11,788
Of course you're my girl.

1038
01:09:11,747 --> 01:09:14,208
Then we can be married,
can't we?

1039
01:09:14,149 --> 01:09:16,192
I guess so.

1040
01:09:16,148 --> 01:09:18,026
No. If I'm not
good enough to marry...

1041
01:09:17,989 --> 01:09:19,950
I'm not good enough to kiss.

1042
01:09:19,910 --> 01:09:21,536
Come here, you bobtailed
little tree cat.

1043
01:09:21,511 --> 01:09:22,969
We're bespoken, ain't we?

1044
01:09:22,951 --> 01:09:25,244
It wouldn't do no harm
to tell folks, would it?

1045
01:09:25,190 --> 01:09:26,650
Sure, we'll tell them.

1046
01:09:26,631 --> 01:09:28,592
Can we tell them soon?

1047
01:09:28,553 --> 01:09:30,471
Can we tell them
Saturday at the barbecue?

1048
01:09:30,433 --> 01:09:32,268
Sure, we can. Why not?

1049
01:09:34,755 --> 01:09:36,715
What you got here?

1050
01:09:36,675 --> 01:09:38,134
Something the sinkiller gave me.

1051
01:09:38,115 --> 01:09:39,741
He said it would keep me...

1052
01:09:39,715 --> 01:09:41,676
sweet and clean
as the first milking.

1053
01:09:43,557 --> 01:09:45,349
Who cares about milking?

1054
01:09:45,318 --> 01:09:47,444
I don't want no milkmaid.

1055
01:09:58,762 --> 01:10:02,222
Don't you get awful tired
eating just beef?

1056
01:10:05,963 --> 01:10:08,424
Wish we could get
an eighty-hour week.

1057
01:10:08,363 --> 01:10:10,323
Yeah. Me, too.

1058
01:10:10,285 --> 01:10:12,244
Kind of miss Jesse
around here. Don't you?

1059
01:10:12,206 --> 01:10:14,458
Jesse? Better not mention
his name on Spanish Bit.

1060
01:10:14,406 --> 01:10:17,076
Can't get over Lem Smoot
joining those railroad people.

1061
01:10:17,007 --> 01:10:18,967
I always say, if you can't
whip them, join them.

1062
01:10:18,927 --> 01:10:20,387
Never saw so many crows...

1063
01:10:20,367 --> 01:10:22,828
around here before
in all my life.

1064
01:10:22,768 --> 01:10:25,729
Wish they'd learn
to grow corn without husks.

1065
01:10:29,490 --> 01:10:31,450
Wouldn't surprise me none
if that Indian girl...

1066
01:10:31,410 --> 01:10:34,371
didn't up and massacre
the whole dern lot of them.

1067
01:10:34,292 --> 01:10:35,751
When I'm married...

1068
01:10:35,732 --> 01:10:38,693
I'm gonna have
lots and lots of parties.

1069
01:10:38,612 --> 01:10:43,074
But who would do all the work
when I gives my party?

1070
01:10:42,934 --> 01:10:45,394
I likes fishing better
than I does dancing.

1071
01:10:45,335 --> 01:10:47,295
You never go fishing.

1072
01:10:47,255 --> 01:10:49,925
I never goes dancing neither.

1073
01:10:49,856 --> 01:10:52,108
The gals to the center
and ring to the left.

1074
01:10:52,055 --> 01:10:54,016
The boys shake hands
and go to the right.

1075
01:10:53,977 --> 01:10:56,938
Now weave a basket.
Circle left.

1076
01:10:56,858 --> 01:11:00,320
Now we'll weave that basket
the other way.

1077
01:11:00,219 --> 01:11:02,179
Senator, they
appreciate it very much.

1078
01:11:02,140 --> 01:11:05,101
I try to show my people
a good time, eh, Lewt?

1079
01:11:05,020 --> 01:11:06,980
You bet your boots, Senator.

1080
01:11:06,942 --> 01:11:09,401
Now, birdie in the center
and seven hands around.

1081
01:11:09,342 --> 01:11:12,135
Bird hop out,
and the crow hop in.

1082
01:11:12,063 --> 01:11:14,022
She around the she,
and the he around the he.

1083
01:11:13,983 --> 01:11:16,110
The he around the she,
and the she around the he.

1084
01:11:16,063 --> 01:11:17,690
Four hands up, and here we go.

1085
01:11:17,664 --> 01:11:19,124
Hurry up, boys,
and don't be slow.

1086
01:11:19,104 --> 01:11:21,565
'Cause you'll never get
your love if you don't do so.

1087
01:11:30,868 --> 01:11:33,329
Pearl, dear, I've been
looking all over for you.

1088
01:11:33,268 --> 01:11:35,729
You should be downstairs.
It's very rude.

1089
01:11:35,669 --> 01:11:37,129
I'm sorry.

1090
01:11:37,109 --> 01:11:39,570
I was fixing my hair
the way you told me to.

1091
01:11:39,509 --> 01:11:40,969
Do I look all right, ma'am?

1092
01:11:40,951 --> 01:11:43,410
You're the prettiest girl
at the party.

1093
01:11:43,353 --> 01:11:45,313
Here, dear. Wear this.

1094
01:11:45,272 --> 01:11:50,276
You're so kind to me...
this dress and everything.

1095
01:11:55,356 --> 01:11:57,815
Come, dear.

1096
01:11:57,756 --> 01:12:00,758
Oh, ma'am! What's the matter?

1097
01:12:02,237 --> 01:12:05,073
It's nothing. Let's go.

1098
01:12:06,358 --> 01:12:10,862
Balance your partners,
and two ladies cross

