Put your left foot,
put your left foot

1160
01:14:25,598 --> 01:14:28,352
Put your left foot just so

1161
01:14:28,279 --> 01:14:31,782
Take a step to the side,
take a step to...

1162
01:14:31,680 --> 01:14:33,140
Come on, honey.

1163
01:14:33,120 --> 01:14:35,081
Don't let them yokels
laugh at you.

1164
01:14:35,041 --> 01:14:36,834
But I don't know how.

1165
01:14:36,801 --> 01:14:38,804
It's easy. Just follow me.

1166
01:14:54,247 --> 01:14:56,249
Now you're doing it.

1167
01:15:20,134 --> 01:15:22,595
Won't they be surprised
when they hear about us?

1168
01:15:22,534 --> 01:15:24,202
When they hear what about us?

1169
01:15:24,175 --> 01:15:25,927
That we're bespoken, of course.

1170
01:15:25,895 --> 01:15:27,355
Oh, that.

1171
01:15:27,335 --> 01:15:29,796
But that's what you said.
You said we'd tell them tonight.

1172
01:15:29,736 --> 01:15:31,697
Just as everything
is going good...

1173
01:15:31,658 --> 01:15:33,617
you got to go
and start all that again.

1174
01:15:33,579 --> 01:15:37,540
Either you tell people
we're bespoken, or I will.

1175
01:15:44,140 --> 01:15:46,101
I want to tell you
something...

1176
01:15:46,062 --> 01:15:47,521
you don't fool me none no more.

1177
01:15:47,502 --> 01:15:49,461
Will you stop
poking up and vexing me?

1178
01:15:49,423 --> 01:15:51,883
I don't know how a man
stands it, the way you go on.

1179
01:15:51,823 --> 01:15:53,783
You think you don't
have to marry me.

1180
01:15:53,744 --> 01:15:55,705
Maybe you don't.
And you don't have to go on...

1181
01:15:55,665 --> 01:15:57,625
lying to me no more neither.
I made up my mind.

1182
01:15:57,586 --> 01:15:59,545
You made up your mind
about what?

1183
01:15:59,506 --> 01:16:00,965
Just like I said...

1184
01:16:00,946 --> 01:16:02,907
if you won't marry me,
I'll get out.

1185
01:16:02,867 --> 01:16:04,327
I'll go away as fast as I can.

1186
01:16:04,307 --> 01:16:06,267
You can go and keep
going for all I care.

1187
01:16:06,228 --> 01:16:08,188
Go find yourself
somebody else to pester.

1188
01:16:08,147 --> 01:16:10,108
But don't you care?

1189
01:16:10,068 --> 01:16:11,944
No woman can tie
onto me like that...

1190
01:16:11,909 --> 01:16:16,371
least of all a bobtail
little half-breed like you.

1191
01:16:16,230 --> 01:16:20,192
All righty.
Thanks for letting me know...

1192
01:16:20,073 --> 01:16:22,575
how you think about me.

1193
01:16:25,913 --> 01:16:27,790
El Paso and Amarillo
ain't no different...

1194
01:16:27,754 --> 01:16:29,214
than Sodom and Gomorra...

1195
01:16:29,194 --> 01:16:30,654
on a smaller scale,
of course, but...

1196
01:16:30,634 --> 01:16:33,345
What in Beezelbub's name
do you call that?

1197
01:16:44,558 --> 01:16:48,562
I wasn't having a very good time
at the party neither.

1198
01:16:49,840 --> 01:16:54,052
I was just kind of tired.
Who are you?

1199
01:16:53,921 --> 01:16:56,131
I'm the new
straw boss around here.

1200
01:16:56,082 --> 01:16:58,918
Name's Pierce.
Sam to my friends.

1201
01:16:58,842 --> 01:17:00,718
Mind if I sit down?

1202
01:17:00,683 --> 01:17:01,766
If you want.

1203
01:17:03,604 --> 01:17:06,565
Must be plenty tiring
on a person, all that dancing.

1204
01:17:06,486 --> 01:17:08,613
- Don't you dance?
- No, ma'am.

1205
01:17:08,566 --> 01:17:10,984
Somehow, I never got
the chance to learn.

1206
01:17:10,885 --> 01:17:12,888
You ought to. It's fun.

1207
01:17:12,807 --> 01:17:15,809
Lots of folks seem to think so.

1208
01:17:15,687 --> 01:17:17,689
How would you like
to learn tonight?

1209
01:17:17,608 --> 01:17:19,610
What? Do you mean
you'd teach me?

1210
01:17:19,529 --> 01:17:22,032
I ain't so good at them
fancy dances myself...

1211
01:17:21,930 --> 01:17:24,264
but we could learn
together, if you want.

1212
01:17:24,169 --> 01:17:27,130
- I'd be right honored.
- Then come on.

1213
01:17:28,251 --> 01:17:30,004
Come on!

1214
01:17:40,175 --> 01:17:43,636
The next dance
will be ladies choice.

1215
01:17:43,536 --> 01:17:45,537
The ladies choose the gents.

1216
01:17:45,455 --> 01:17:47,957
Gents line up
over on this side...

1217
01:17:47,857 --> 01:17:49,860
ladies over yonder.

1218
01:17:49,779 --> 01:17:52,906
Now, ladies,
this is your big chance.

1219
01:17:52,819 --> 01:17:56,947
And don't be afraid to go after
the true love of your choice.

1220
01:17:56,820 --> 01:17:58,321
I'd rather play me some poker.

1221
01:17:58,260 --> 01:17:59,887
Females shouldn't be
allowed no choice.

1222
01:17:59,860 --> 01:18:01,361
It ain't decent.

1223
01:18:01,300 --> 01:18:03,636
I'll bet you six bits
that fat one grabs me.

1224
01:18:03,541 --> 01:18:06,168
You leave Jake alone.
You had him all evening.

1225
01:18:06,102 --> 01:18:08,020
Of all the nerve!

1226
01:18:11,184 --> 01:18:14,438
When I stomp my heels
three times...

1227
01:18:14,345 --> 01:18:16,347
run for the gent of your choice.

1228
01:18:16,305 --> 01:18:19,809
Ready? One, two... scat!

1229
01:18:55,516 --> 01:18:58,519
I want you to get acquainted
with little Lewt...

1230
01:18:58,438 --> 01:19:02,357
the longest-legged critter
this side of the main house.

1231
01:19:02,239 --> 01:19:04,198
He's so cute!

1232
01:19:04,159 --> 01:19:06,245
A lot cuter than big Lewt.

1233
01:19:11,000 --> 01:19:13,920
He's just like silk.

1234
01:19:20,404 --> 01:19:22,365
There you are, ma.

1235
01:19:25,405 --> 01:19:27,866
Want to see the others?

1236
01:19:27,805 --> 01:19:31,059
Yes. And I'm gonna help you
take care of them, too.

1237
01:19:30,966 --> 01:19:32,509
Sure, you are.

1238
01:19:33,687 --> 01:19:35,480
Ain't they wonderful,
these babies?

1239
01:19:35,448 --> 01:19:36,907
Any kind of babies.

1240
01:19:36,888 --> 01:19:38,347
They sure are.

1241
01:19:38,329 --> 01:19:41,165
I remember reading something
once when I was a kid.

1242
01:19:42,491 --> 01:19:43,617
What?

1243
01:19:43,610 --> 01:19:44,903
You'd think I was silly...

1244
01:19:44,891 --> 01:19:47,185
a big galoot like me
spouting poetry.

1245
01:19:47,131 --> 01:19:48,758
No, Sam. Please.

1246
01:19:48,732 --> 01:19:52,361
I'm going to sit right here
until you tell me.

1247
01:19:52,253 --> 01:19:55,256
It goes something like this.

1248
01:19:56,574 --> 01:20:01,370
For everything created in
the bounds of earth and sky...

1249
01:20:01,214 --> 01:20:04,175
has such longing to be mated.

1250
01:20:04,097 --> 01:20:07,558
It must couple or must die.

1251
01:20:07,458 --> 01:20:10,419
That's the best poem
I ever heard.

1252
01:20:10,338 --> 01:20:12,799
I'm glad you like it.

1253
01:20:12,739 --> 01:20:14,699
You married?

1254
01:20:14,660 --> 01:20:18,955
Nope. Never run across
anybody I wanted to marry.

1255
01:20:18,820 --> 01:20:21,947
Besides, I never got up
nerve enough to ask anybody.

1256
01:20:21,862 --> 01:20:24,823
I guess you must be
getting pretty old.

1257
01:20:24,742 --> 01:20:28,704
Yep. Old enough to be
your father... and then some.

1258
01:20:28,583 --> 01:20:30,543
Why?

1259
01:20:30,504 --> 01:20:31,922
Nothing.

1260
01:20:33,065 --> 01:20:34,525
I guess, just the same...

1261
01:20:34,505 --> 01:20:37,967
there are plenty of women
who would marry you anyway.

1262
01:20:37,865 --> 01:20:39,825
I better be getting home.

1263
01:20:39,746 --> 01:20:43,041
Mrs. McCanles is kind of ailing.

1264
01:20:48,908 --> 01:20:51,703
You wouldn't marry me,
would you?

1265
01:20:51,630 --> 01:20:55,092
- What did you say?
- I said, would you marry me?

1266
01:20:54,991 --> 01:20:56,951
Don't get mad, please.

1267
01:20:56,912 --> 01:20:59,040
First time in my life
I got up some nerve.

1268
01:20:58,992 --> 01:21:00,743
How could a big galoot...

1269
01:21:00,713 --> 01:21:02,673
