You don't know about me.

1270
01:21:02,632 --> 01:21:04,092
If you did, you wouldn't ask.

1271
01:21:04,072 --> 01:21:05,532
You mean about Lewt?

1272
01:21:05,514 --> 01:21:07,973
So you know about
me and Lewt, too?

1273
01:21:07,915 --> 01:21:09,875
Yeah, I guess
ain't nobody don't know.

1274
01:21:09,835 --> 01:21:11,795
I've knocked around plenty...

1275
01:21:11,755 --> 01:21:14,716
- I'm trash, I tell you.
- Don't go telling me that.

1276
01:21:14,636 --> 01:21:17,097
I'd kill the first man
who said anything like that.

1277
01:21:17,037 --> 01:21:20,499
But I don't love you.
Don't that matter?

1278
01:21:20,399 --> 01:21:22,358
You've only known me
a little while.

1279
01:21:22,319 --> 01:21:24,279
I know I'm not something
girls dream about...

1280
01:21:24,239 --> 01:21:25,699
like the McCanleses.

1281
01:21:25,679 --> 01:21:28,140
- I'm not rich like them either.
- It ain't that.

1282
01:21:28,080 --> 01:21:30,041
But I'd love you,
and I'd take care of you.

1283
01:21:30,000 --> 01:21:31,960
I got a little money saved.

1284
01:21:31,922 --> 01:21:33,881
Get a little ranch
of our own, maybe.

1285
01:21:33,842 --> 01:21:37,304
Won't you even think
about it, honey? Please, honey.

1286
01:21:37,203 --> 01:21:39,163
Don't you call me "honey."

1287
01:21:39,124 --> 01:21:41,751
Lewt called me that.
You're all alike!

1288
01:21:48,246 --> 01:21:49,706
Coming?

1289
01:21:51,646 --> 01:21:56,067
I hope I didn't say nothing
to hurt your feelings.

1290
01:21:55,928 --> 01:21:58,347
That's all right.

1291
01:22:01,130 --> 01:22:03,591
I'll marry you
if you still want me to.

1292
01:22:03,530 --> 01:22:05,032
You mean it?

1293
01:22:30,739 --> 01:22:32,531
I declare. I never saw...

1294
01:22:32,499 --> 01:22:34,792
so many cows before
in all my life.

1295
01:22:34,739 --> 01:22:37,200
I'm afraid they're not
all cows, Helen.

1296
01:22:37,140 --> 01:22:39,101
Sometimes, my dear, I think...

1297
01:22:39,061 --> 01:22:41,021
that I didn't
bring you up properly.

1298
01:22:40,982 --> 01:22:44,150
All right. I understand.
All I need is a hint.

1299
01:22:59,627 --> 01:23:02,046
Those steers
are from Spanish Bit.

1300
01:23:01,988 --> 01:23:04,490
I thought your father's ranch
was hundreds of miles from here.

1301
01:23:04,427 --> 01:23:06,263
See? There's the brand.
They're on their way to market.

1302
01:23:11,631 --> 01:23:13,633
If it ain't
the big railroad man.

1303
01:23:13,551 --> 01:23:15,553
How's everything at the Bit?

1304
01:23:15,472 --> 01:23:18,474
Getting along just fine
since you left... Mr. McCanles.

1305
01:23:18,352 --> 01:23:19,853
Same old Sid.

1306
01:23:19,792 --> 01:23:22,294
I'll be inside, darling.
Come, father.

1307
01:23:22,193 --> 01:23:23,696
Hey, that Langford's daughter?

1308
01:23:23,635 --> 01:23:25,136
Heard you were
kind of sweet on her.

1309
01:23:25,075 --> 01:23:26,408
Yes, that's Miss Langford.

1310
01:23:26,354 --> 01:23:27,689
Pretty, ain't she?

1311
01:23:27,634 --> 01:23:29,135
We could use a few like her
around the ranch...

1312
01:23:29,074 --> 01:23:30,576
especially now that
Pearl's going... maybe.

1313
01:23:30,516 --> 01:23:32,018
What do you mean?

1314
01:23:31,957 --> 01:23:33,791
Darnest thing you ever heard.
She's getting married.

1315
01:23:33,717 --> 01:23:35,720
Can you imagine
anybody marrying Pearl?

1316
01:23:35,639 --> 01:23:37,140
Is she marrying Lewt?

1317
01:23:37,079 --> 01:23:39,080
Lewt? What would Lewt...

1318
01:23:38,998 --> 01:23:41,000
Nah, she's marrying Sam Pierce.

1319
01:23:40,919 --> 01:23:42,921
Pearl ought to be
very happy with Sam.

1320
01:23:42,840 --> 01:23:44,841
She ain't marrying him yet.

1321
01:23:44,760 --> 01:23:46,762
She ain't marrying nobody...

1322
01:23:46,680 --> 01:23:49,682
until Lewt decides
to give the bride away.

1323
01:23:49,560 --> 01:23:51,563
So long, Judas.

1324
01:23:52,963 --> 01:23:55,340
Can't say I like...

1325
01:23:55,284 --> 01:23:59,244
your Spanish Bit people
very much, if he's any criteria.

1326
01:23:59,125 --> 01:24:00,918
Darling, I've been thinking.

1327
01:24:00,885 --> 01:24:03,346
Why couldn't there be a spur
track right on Spanish Bit?

1328
01:24:03,286 --> 01:24:05,246
Then they could
just ship the cattle...

1329
01:24:05,206 --> 01:24:07,833
instead of driving them
all that distance.

1330
01:24:07,766 --> 01:24:09,726
You're not even
listening to me, dear.

1331
01:24:09,688 --> 01:24:12,147
Certainly I am.
You were saying...

1332
01:24:12,088 --> 01:24:15,924
You were asking if...
What were you saying?

1333
01:24:15,810 --> 01:24:17,227
I was trying to prove...

1334
01:24:17,210 --> 01:24:18,836
what a helpful wife
I'm going to be.

1335
01:24:18,810 --> 01:24:20,311
Give me a kiss.

1336
01:24:21,692 --> 01:24:23,651
I couldn't help overhearing.

1337
01:24:23,612 --> 01:24:24,571
What?

1338
01:24:24,572 --> 01:24:26,531
You liked that girl, didn't you?

1339
01:24:26,493 --> 01:24:27,952
You still like her?

1340
01:24:27,933 --> 01:24:29,893
I'm sure I'll always
be devoted to her.

1341
01:24:29,852 --> 01:24:31,813
Hope you'll like her, too.

1342
01:24:31,773 --> 01:24:33,858
But you were in love
with her, weren't you?

1343
01:24:33,814 --> 01:24:36,192
Yes, I was in love with her.

1344
01:24:38,016 --> 01:24:40,518
I said I was.

1345
01:24:44,257 --> 01:24:46,218
Jesse. Father.

1346
01:24:46,178 --> 01:24:50,515
Sometimes I think he didn't
bring you up properly.

1347
01:24:51,700 --> 01:24:55,328
What were you worried about
when I came out just now?

1348
01:24:55,220 --> 01:24:59,140
Worried? I was just wondering
what my brother Lewt might do.

1349
01:25:21,627 --> 01:25:24,588
Zeke, where's
my peppermint and soda?

1350
01:25:24,509 --> 01:25:25,969
Coming up now.

1351
01:25:25,951 --> 01:25:27,910
Hear you named the day.

1352
01:25:27,870 --> 01:25:29,330
That's right.

1353
01:25:29,310 --> 01:25:31,771
Ring just come in the last post.

1354
01:25:31,711 --> 01:25:32,671
Mighty pretty. Yep.

1355
01:25:32,671 --> 01:25:34,631
You sure are shot full of luck.

1356
01:25:34,592 --> 01:25:36,552
I'd like to stand
the drinks for everybody.

1357
01:25:36,512 --> 01:25:38,473
I'm getting married
in the morning.

1358
01:25:38,433 --> 01:25:39,892
That's fine.

1359
01:25:39,873 --> 01:25:41,875
Save your money, Pierce.

1360
01:25:49,516 --> 01:25:51,768
So you figure
you got yourself a wife.

1361
01:25:51,717 --> 01:25:53,802
I don't figure. I know I have.

1362
01:25:53,757 --> 01:25:55,718
Think you can keep her?

1363
01:25:55,678 --> 01:25:57,888
Reckon as how I can.

1364
01:25:57,839 --> 01:26:00,048
Cattle rustlers
and women rustlers.

1365
01:26:00,000 --> 01:26:01,792
Both of them steal...

1366
01:26:01,760 --> 01:26:03,678
what's got another man's
brand on it.

1367
01:26:03,640 --> 01:26:07,727
I don't think I like
the way you're talking.

1368
01:26:07,601 --> 01:26:09,644
Maybe I didn't rightly
understand you.

1369
01:26:09,603 --> 01:26:12,813
Yeah, you understand me
all right.

1370
01:26:12,723 --> 01:26:17,436
Pearl Chavez is my girl,
and she'll always be my girl...

1371
01:26:17,284 --> 01:26:20,036
just as long
as I want her to be.

1372
01:26:26,407 --> 01:26:30,243
From now you, you're gonna
respect Pearl's name.

1373
01:26:30,087 --> 01:26:33,715
If that ain't
the best joke yet.

1374
01:26:33,609 --> 01:26:37,988
He's defending the lady's name...
my girl's name.

1375
01:26:49,454 --> 01:26:51,330
Has anybody else around here...

1376
01:26:51,294 --> 01:26:54,796
got any fancy ideas
about Pearl Chavez?

1377
01:26:59,137 --> 01:27:01,472
Don't seem to be no takers.

1378
01:27:13,861 --> 01:27:17,530
I don't rightly know
much about Sam Pierce, O Lord...

1379
01:27:17,421 --> 01:27:19,174
but from what I hear...

1380
01:27:19,143 --> 01:27:22,188
he'll be needing
no introduction to you.

1381
01:27:22,103 --> 01:27:24,480
Seeing as how Sam was snatched
from his loved ones' arms...

1382
01:27:24,423 --> 01:27:27,009
before they even had time
to get a good grip on him...

1383
01:27:26,943 --> 01:27:29,321
I'm counting on you to give him
a better break up yonder.

1384
01:27:30,666 --> 01:27:32,125
Hey, you hatchet face!

1385
01:27:32,106 --> 01:27:34,066
Are you so almighty hungry
to hang one man...

1386
01:27:34,026 --> 01:27:36,946
that you can't wait till we
get through planting this one?

1387
01:27:38,347 --> 01:27:41,392
Now I be consigning him
to your keeping.

1388
01:27:41,309 --> 01:27:43,437
And I'm guessing
you'll find him...

1389
01:27:43,389 --> 01:27:45,349
the gentlest,
sweetest straw boss...

1390
01:27:45,310 --> 01:27:48,437
ever to enter the pearly gates.

1391
01:27:48,351 --> 01:27:49,852
Amen.

1392
01:27:51,711 --> 01:27:54,714
Start shoveling, cowpokes.

1393
01:28:06,116 --> 01:28:09,578
It's our fault.
We raised him wild.

1394
01:28:09,477 --> 01:28:12,480
If he'd only gone
to school, like Jesse.

1395
01:28:12,358 --> 01:28:15,987
I thought I asked you never
to mention Jesse's name again.

1396
01:28:15,879 --> 01:28:17,214
It's true.

1397
01:28:17,159 --> 01:28:19,661
You spoiled Lewt, and I let you.

1398
01:28:19,560 --> 01:28:21,561
Ever since he was a child...

1399
01:28:21,480 --> 01:28:24,483
he thought rules
weren't made for him.

1400
01:28:24,361 --> 01:28:26,988
He thought you made
the rules, all of them...

1401
01:28:26,922 --> 01:28:29,258
not just those
for Spanish Bit.

1402
01:28:29,163 --> 01:28:30,664
It's that Indian girl.

1403
01:28:30,603 --> 01:28:32,604
If you hadn't
brought her here...

1404
01:28:32,523 --> 01:28:34,525
none of this
would have happened.

1405
01:28:34,444 --> 01:28:37,446
Perhaps if your attitude
toward her had been different...

1406
01:28:37,324 --> 01:28:40,244
It's my fault, huh?
It's my fault.

1407
01:28:40,165 --> 01:28:43,627
You dared to bring
that Indian baggage...

1408
01:28:43,526 --> 01:28:47,989
right here into this house,
and now you try to tell me...

1409
01:28:47,848 --> 01:28:50,309
You get her out of here.

1410
01:28:50,249 --> 01:28:54,211
And what's more,
get her out of here tonight!

1411
01:28:54,090 --> 01:28:58,052
You've screamed at me
for the last time.

1412
01:28:57,930 --> 01:29:01,892
You made one of your sons
hate you and sent him away.

1413
01:29:01,771 --> 01:29:04,775
You made the other one
a... murderer.

1414
01:29:06,093 --> 01:29:10,680
Pearl will stay here
just as long as I do.

1415
01:29:31,540 --> 01:29:34,501
Here's the money.
You better clear out of here...

1416
01:29:34,422 --> 01:29:36,382
until this thing blows over.

1417
01:29:36,342 --> 01:29:37,761
Thanks, pa.

1418
01:29:37,742 --> 01:29:39,744
It's gonna take
plenty of fixing.

1419
01:29:39,702 --> 01:29:42,163
So you better
stay away from here...

1420
01:29:42,104 --> 01:29:45,064
until I send you the word.

1421
01:29:44,985 --> 01:29:47,946
It'll take a year maybe.

1422
01:29:47,865 --> 01:29:49,825
Maybe more than that even.

1423
01:29:49,786 --> 01:29:52,246
I'm sorry to cause you
all this trouble.

1424
01:29:52,186 --> 01:29:54,146
If you get me out of this one...

1425
01:29:54,106 --> 01:29:56,066
Never mind that.

1426
01:29:56,028 --> 01:29:59,990
I ain't counting
on no reformation.

1427
01:29:59,869 --> 01:30:01,996
Go on. Get going fast.

1428
01:30:01,949 --> 01:30:03,743
Good-bye, pa.

1429
01:30:03,709 --> 01:30:05,169
So long, Sid.

1430
01:30:05,150 --> 01:30:06,653
So long, Lewt.

1431
01:30:08,032 --> 01:30:10,992
Take care of yourself, son.

1432
01:30:10,912 --> 01:30:12,914
I will, pa.

1433
01:30:27,237 --> 01:30:29,197
Yay, boy.

1434
01:30:29,157 --> 01:30:32,035
Now here's a chance
to do something for pa.

1435
01:31:55,943 --> 01:31:59,905
I've been working
on the railroad

1436
01:31:59,784 --> 01:32:03,245
All the live-long day

1437
01:32:06,505 --> 01:32:08,465
Come on, Sid. Come on.

1438
01:32:08,425 --> 01:32:11,386
You ain't got the mint
on this game.

1439
01:32:11,307 --> 01:32:13,267
Sorry, Senator.

1440
01:32:13,227 --> 01:32:17,105
You certainly stuck your head
in a noose that time.

1441
01:32:18,349 --> 01:32:19,767
Pearl, honey.

1442
01:32:22,111 --> 01:32:24,654
What you doing with that thing?

1443
01:32:24,590 --> 01:32:26,343
There ain't nobody here but me.

1444
01:32:26,311 --> 01:32:29,439
I'm gonna kill you.

1445
01:32:29,351 --> 01:32:32,937
That wouldn't be a very ladylike
thing to do, would it...

1446
01:32:32,833 --> 01:32:35,501
after me riding thirty miles
just for a kiss?

1447
01:32:35,434 --> 01:32:38,018
You're gonna get
what you gave Sam Pierce.

1448
01:32:37,955 --> 01:32:39,414
That just goes to show you...

1449
01:32:39,395 --> 01:32:41,313
there ain't no gratitude
for nothing.

1450
01:32:41,275 --> 01:32:43,945
If it wasn't for me,
you'd be tied up...

1451
01:32:43,876 --> 01:32:47,337
with that brokendown
cowhand right now.

1452
01:32:47,237 --> 01:32:50,697
You might as well marry pa.

1453
01:32:50,598 --> 01:32:54,517
Sam Pierce was a good man,
and you're a skunk.

1454
01:32:54,398 --> 01:32:55,900
Of all the ornery females.

1455
01:32:55,879 --> 01:32:57,339
One minute you're yammering...

1456
01:32:57,319 --> 01:32:58,779
because I don't
love you enough...

1457
01:32:58,759 --> 01:33:01,220
and when I go out
and show you how much I do...

1458
01:33:01,161 --> 01:33:03,163
you're wanting to plug me.

1459
01:33:05,003 --> 01:33:07,213
You're my girl, honey.

1460
01:33:07,162 --> 01:33:08,873
I was your girl.

1461
01:33:08,843 --> 01:33:12,304
Anybody who was my girl
is still my girl.

1462
01:33:12,205 --> 01:33:15,165
That's the kind of guy I am.

1463
01:33:15,085 --> 01:33:17,044
You know... loyal.

1464
01:33:17,006 --> 01:33:18,466
Stay back.

1465
01:33:18,446 --> 01:33:21,949
There ain't nobody
gonna take my girl.

1466
01:33:24,208 --> 01:33:25,710
Nobody.

1467
01:33:29,250 --> 01:33:30,835
Never.

1468
01:33:33,251 --> 01:33:34,877
I'm saving you, tiger cat.

1469
01:33:34,851 --> 01:33:37,979
Just when I figure
I'm doing fine and dandy...

1470
01:33:37,891 --> 01:33:42,521
I start thinking about you,
and nothing else is any good.

1471
01:33:47,174 --> 01:33:49,593
Here.

1472
01:33:51,015 --> 01:33:52,683
What's going on around here?

1473
01:33:53,897 --> 01:33:55,523
Come in.

1474
01:33:55,496 --> 01:33:56,831
Howdy, Senator.

1475
01:33:56,777 --> 01:33:59,363
Sorry to be busting in
on you like this.

1476
01:33:59,297 --> 01:34:01,799
It's all right, sheriff.
How's tricks?

1477
01:34:01,739 --> 01:34:03,531
How's the law-breaking
business?

1478
01:34:03,499 --> 01:34:06,001
Pretty quiet... since Lewt left.

1479
01:34:05,900 --> 01:34:07,901
Yeah, pretty dull
without him around.

1480
01:34:07,820 --> 01:34:10,823
Ain't heard from him lately,
have you, Senator?

1481
01:34:10,701 --> 01:34:14,538
Lewt? Here. Have a bite.

1482
01:34:15,662 --> 01:34:17,497
Don't mind if I do.

1483
01:34:17,423 --> 01:34:19,425
Wish I could afford this brand.

1484
01:34:19,344 --> 01:34:22,346
The next batch I get,
I'll send you some.

1485
01:34:22,224 --> 01:34:25,227
No, I ain't heard
a word from Lewt...

1486
01:34:25,105 --> 01:34:30,026
since he was attacked
by that no-account Sam Pierce.

1487
01:34:29,865 --> 01:34:32,826
How's your other son
feel about it?

1488
01:34:32,748 --> 01:34:34,624
I ain't got no other son.

1489
01:34:36,109 --> 01:34:38,069
Funny thing... one of the boys...

1490
01:34:41,750 --> 01:34:44,878
Lewt? I wish it was so.

1491
01:34:44,791 --> 01:34:47,377
Don't mind if I have
a look around, do you?

1492
01:34:47,311 --> 01:34:50,773
No. Go ahead, sheriff.
You got your duties to do.

1493
01:34:50,672 --> 01:34:53,342
I'm sorry you're gonna have
your trouble for nothing.

1494
01:34:54,675 --> 01:34:57,511
I hear Mrs. McCanles
has been feeling kind of poorly.

1495
01:34:57,435 --> 01:34:58,936
It ain't nothing.

1496
01:34:58,915 --> 01:35:01,041
Just getting
a little old, I guess.

1497
01:35:00,996 --> 01:35:02,706
You reckon the missus
would mind...

1498
01:35:02,676 --> 01:35:04,844
if I kind of
looked around her room?

1499
01:35:04,797 --> 01:35:06,382
No. Why should she mind?

1500
01:35:06,357 --> 01:35:07,733
Go ahead.

1501
01:35:07,717 --> 01:35:09,678
Sid, ain't you moved yet?

1502
01:35:13,879 --> 01:35:15,255
Come in.

1503
01:35:16,601 --> 01:35:18,227
- Evening, ma'am.
- Sheriff.

1504
01:35:18,200 --> 01:35:20,369
Sorry to disturb
your privacy, ma'am.

1505
01:35:20,321 --> 01:35:21,906
Sheriff Thompson, what is it?

1506
01:35:21,881 --> 01:35:23,841
It's really nothing, ma'am.

1507
01:35:23,803 --> 01:35:25,762
One of the boys
had a fool notion...

1508
01:35:25,723 --> 01:35:27,684
that Lewt was around here.

1509
01:35:27,643 --> 01:35:29,603
I'm afraid if Lewton
were around...

1510
01:35:29,564 --> 01:35:32,233
I'd be the last person
to know it.

1511
01:35:32,164 --> 01:35:33,457
Sorry.

1512
01:35:47,729 --> 01:35:50,190
Oh, my sons.

1513
01:35:50,130 --> 01:35:52,132
My sons.

1514
01:35:53,850 --> 01:35:55,394
Let's try this one.

1515
01:35:59,253 --> 01:36:00,879
Who's that?

1516
01:36:00,852 --> 01:36:02,354
Is that you, girl?

1517
01:36:03,894 --> 01:36:05,520
What do you want?

1518
01:36:05,495 --> 01:36:08,956
It's me... Sheriff Thompson.
You ain't seen Lewt, have you?

1519
01:36:08,855 --> 01:36:11,816
Lewt? That murdering,
sneaking no-account.

1520
01:36:11,736 --> 01:36:13,696
I wish I could see him.

1521
01:36:13,657 --> 01:36:15,908
I reckon you do.

1522
01:36:15,857 --> 01:36:18,026
I was forgetting
about Sam Pierce.

1523
01:36:17,977 --> 01:36:19,062
Sorry.

1524
01:36:19,058 --> 01:36:22,936
Good night.
See you at the hanging.

1525
01:36:32,103 --> 01:36:33,520
Poor old Mac.

1526
01:36:33,462 --> 01:36:36,590
He don't know how close he came
to getting plugged.

1527
01:36:36,503 --> 01:36:39,130
Be quiet. It ain't safe yet.

1528
01:36:39,064 --> 01:36:40,899
It ain't safe for them,
you mean.

1529
01:36:40,864 --> 01:36:42,867
There they go now.

1530
01:36:44,346 --> 01:36:46,348
I think I'll light out
for Mexico.

1531
01:36:46,306 --> 01:36:47,766
Mexico?

1532
01:36:47,707 --> 01:36:48,915
Yeah.

1533
01:36:48,908 --> 01:36:50,618
I'm gonna grab me a ranch...

1534
01:36:50,587 --> 01:36:53,089
that'll make this place
look like a gopher hole.

1535
01:36:53,027 --> 01:36:56,281
It would be like heaven,
being in Mexico together.

1536
01:36:56,188 --> 01:36:58,315
I'll show these
heel-squatters around here...

1537
01:36:58,270 --> 01:36:59,896
a thing or two about ranching.

1538
01:36:59,870 --> 01:37:01,205
You can do it, too.

1539
01:37:01,190 --> 01:37:03,151
- Lewt.
- Huh?

1540
01:37:03,110 --> 01:37:06,530
- Go saddle my pinto.
- What for?

1541
01:37:06,431 --> 01:37:09,893
- While I get ready.
- Ready for what?

1542
01:37:09,792 --> 01:37:13,254
I'm going with you, of course.
Hurry up.

1543
01:37:15,075 --> 01:37:17,410
You wouldn't like it
down there, honey.

1544
01:37:17,315 --> 01:37:19,149
Sure, I will. I'll be
a big help to you, too.

1545
01:37:19,116 --> 01:37:21,201
I can cook, and I can shoot
as good as you...

1546
01:37:21,156 --> 01:37:22,783
and I never get tired riding.

1547
01:37:22,756 --> 01:37:24,382
You'll try to stop me
from doing things...

1548
01:37:24,357 --> 01:37:25,816
yammering about me
maybe getting shot...

1549
01:37:25,797 --> 01:37:27,423
or start all over again
about marrying somebody.

1550
01:37:27,397 --> 01:37:30,359
No. I promise I won't never say
another word about marrying.

1551
01:37:30,279 --> 01:37:31,571
You'll probably
want to go with me...

1552
01:37:31,559 --> 01:37:32,852
every time I feel
like going on a bust...

1553
01:37:32,838 --> 01:37:34,048
or playing me some poker.

1554
01:37:34,040 --> 01:37:35,334
I wouldn't, honest.

1555
01:37:35,320 --> 01:37:36,780
Just so long
as I could be near you.

1556
01:37:36,761 --> 01:37:38,388
I'm gonna live my own way.
Nobody's gonna hog-tie me.

1557
01:37:38,362 --> 01:37:39,488
Please.

1558
01:37:39,481 --> 01:37:40,941
I'll come back
every once in a while...

1559
01:37:40,921 --> 01:37:42,215
and see you, like tonight.

1560
01:37:42,202 --> 01:37:43,828
I'll do anything you say.

1561
01:37:43,803 --> 01:37:46,764
Honey, I love you. I'll see you
every time I come back.

1562
01:37:46,683 --> 01:37:48,643
I'll send for you someday.
Honest I will.

1563
01:37:48,604 --> 01:37:50,064
I want to go with you.
I've got to go with you.

1564
01:37:50,044 --> 01:37:51,504
Will you stop your yammering?
I've got to mosey!

1565
01:37:51,484 --> 01:37:53,444
You love me!
You said you loved me!

1566
01:37:53,405 --> 01:37:55,365
Nobody else can have me
because I'm yours!

1567
01:37:55,325 --> 01:37:57,452
I don't want anybody else!
I want you!

1568
01:37:57,408 --> 01:37:59,951
I'm yours!
Nobody else can have me!

1569
01:37:59,887 --> 01:38:01,931
You said nobody ever!
Now take me with you!

1570
01:38:01,888 --> 01:38:04,264
You've got to take me!
Please! Please, honey!

1571
01:38:04,209 --> 01:38:07,420
- Shut up!
- Lewt, honey, please!

1572
01:38:57,144 --> 01:38:59,521
Begging your pardon, ma'am...

1573
01:38:59,464 --> 01:39:01,049
I'd like to say
all us boys at the Bit...

1574
01:39:01,025 --> 01:39:03,026
is praying mighty hard
that you get...

1575
01:39:02,944 --> 01:39:05,948
All right, Ken. All right now.
You just wait downstairs.

1576
01:39:05,827 --> 01:39:07,744
I'll let you know
when I need you.

1577
01:39:08,867 --> 01:39:11,703
Will you thank the boys for me?

1578
01:39:11,588 --> 01:39:14,090
Tell them it isn't
quite as hard to go...

1579
01:39:13,988 --> 01:39:15,491
as they may think.

1580
01:39:15,430 --> 01:39:17,932
What are you
talking that way for?

1581
01:39:17,831 --> 01:39:20,833
Anybody would think
you was dying.

1582
01:39:21,991 --> 01:39:24,618
I'm a nuisance to you
even to the end.

1583
01:39:24,551 --> 01:39:26,553
It's the first time
you've been in this room...

1584
01:39:26,472 --> 01:39:28,473
since that night.

1585
01:39:28,393 --> 01:39:31,104
Don't bring that up.

1586
01:39:31,035 --> 01:39:34,704
I never had the courage
to discuss it with you before...

1587
01:39:34,594 --> 01:39:36,554
but it doesn't matter now.

1588
01:39:36,516 --> 01:39:38,475
I've paid for my mistake.

1589
01:39:38,436 --> 01:39:40,730
You've hated me
all through the years.

1590
01:39:40,677 --> 01:39:44,305
You paid? What about me,
with these legs?

1591
01:39:44,197 --> 01:39:46,658
As useless as a hog-tied steer.

1592
01:39:46,597 --> 01:39:49,892
And all because you
couldn't stand to be...

1593
01:39:49,800 --> 01:39:51,969
mistress of the biggest
ranch in Texas.

1594
01:39:51,920 --> 01:39:57,008
And why? I'll tell you why.

1595
01:39:56,841 --> 01:39:58,468
Nobody needed to tell me...

1596
01:39:58,442 --> 01:40:00,236
who you was running away to
that night.

1597
01:40:00,202 --> 01:40:03,705
Nobody needed to tell me
you was running to Chavez.

1598
01:40:03,603 --> 01:40:06,355
That's not true. It's not true.

1599
01:40:06,284 --> 01:40:09,245
I was running away,
but not to Scott.

1600
01:40:09,164 --> 01:40:11,124
Not to Scott.

1601
01:40:11,085 --> 01:40:13,045
True or not, you left me.

1602
01:40:13,006 --> 01:40:15,967
And true or not,
I went after you...

1603
01:40:15,888 --> 01:40:21,267
like any lovesick,
half-baked boy would do.

1604
01:40:21,088 --> 01:40:26,093
I'd give anything...
anything to undo it.

1605
01:40:25,930 --> 01:40:31,852
I loved you, Laura Belle.
Yes, sir, I loved you.

1606
01:40:31,651 --> 01:40:34,612
Kept on saying to myself
all through the years...

1607
01:40:34,532 --> 01:40:39,494
that I hated you,
until finally I did hate you.

1608
01:40:39,334 --> 01:40:42,295
In my heart,
I knew all the time...

1609
01:40:42,215 --> 01:40:44,258
it wasn't your fault, though.

1610
01:40:44,215 --> 01:40:45,674
It was my fault.

1611
01:40:45,655 --> 01:40:50,034
It was my jealousy
that made me like I was...

1612
01:40:49,896 --> 01:40:52,357
hard and cruel-like...

1613
01:40:52,297 --> 01:40:55,716
till I guess
you had to leave me.

1614
01:40:55,618 --> 01:41:00,079
I never should have
gone out after you that night.

1615
01:40:59,940 --> 01:41:03,152
But when I found out
you was gone...

1616
01:41:03,060 --> 01:41:05,603
I got to thinking
you was going to him...

1617
01:41:05,541 --> 01:41:07,709
and I couldn't stand it.

1618
01:41:07,662 --> 01:41:12,124
I swore I'd stop you
and bring you back.

1619
01:41:11,983 --> 01:41:13,943
I went crazy.

1620
01:41:13,903 --> 01:41:18,366
Yes, that's what it was.
I just went crazy.

1621
01:41:18,225 --> 01:41:22,187
And I rode through the night
like a drunken Comanche.

1622
01:41:22,066 --> 01:41:26,486
It was my own crazy jealousy
that threw me off that horse.

1623
01:41:26,347 --> 01:41:30,810
Jackson, forgive me.

1624
01:41:30,668 --> 01:41:33,629
Look at me.

1625
01:41:33,548 --> 01:41:37,010
You're my husband... my very own.

1626
01:41:57,555 --> 01:41:59,015
Hiya, boys.

1627
01:41:58,996 --> 01:42:03,624
- It's Jesse.
- Well, I'll be.

1628
01:42:03,478 --> 01:42:07,106
He's got a lot of gall,
coming back here.

1629
01:42:16,761 --> 01:42:19,347
Where do you think you're going?

1630
01:42:19,283 --> 01:42:22,702
I thought I told you
to keep out of my sight.

1631
01:42:22,603 --> 01:42:24,396
I just found out
my mother is dying...

1632
01:42:24,363 --> 01:42:27,033
and I came to see her,
and I intend to see her.

1633
01:42:26,964 --> 01:42:29,216
They tell me
you're the big noise now...

1634
01:42:29,165 --> 01:42:31,333
with them trespassing thieves.

1635
01:42:31,287 --> 01:42:33,705
I hope my good fortune
doesn't distress you too much.

1636
01:42:33,646 --> 01:42:35,774
They're even talking
about putting you...

1637
01:42:35,727 --> 01:42:37,187
up for public office.

1638
01:42:37,167 --> 01:42:38,960
They must pay high
for double-crossers.

1639
01:42:38,929 --> 01:42:40,387
Senator,
let's not discuss that.

1640
01:42:40,369 --> 01:42:42,163
I'm afraid we
see things differently.

1641
01:42:42,129 --> 01:42:43,589
Nothing on earth
would bring me here...

1642
01:42:43,569 --> 01:42:45,862
You're mighty lucky my men
didn't take a shot at you.

1643
01:42:45,810 --> 01:42:47,436
That was their orders.

1644
01:42:47,410 --> 01:42:49,371
I was about to say
that nothing on earth...

1645
01:42:49,330 --> 01:42:51,333
would bring me back here
except mother.

1646
01:42:51,291 --> 01:42:53,209
Is she in her room?

1647
01:42:53,173 --> 01:42:56,133
- No, she ain't in her room.
- Where is she?

1648
01:42:56,054 --> 01:43:02,476
You'll find her right in there,
in a long pine box.

1649
01:43:43,507 --> 01:43:45,175
Hello, Vashti.

1650
01:43:46,547 --> 01:43:48,549
- Mr. Jesse...
- No, thank you.

1651
01:43:48,468 --> 01:43:50,762
But Mrs. McCanles,
she said to me once...

1652
01:43:50,708 --> 01:43:53,711
"Vashti, you be sure and see
that Mr. Jesse eats proper..."

1653
01:43:53,589 --> 01:43:57,926
You've been a good friend.
I shan't forget it.

1654
01:43:59,351 --> 01:44:02,353
Poor Mrs. McCanles.

1655
01:44:02,232 --> 01:44:05,694
I wonder if Miss Pearl
would mind if you woke her up.

1656
01:44:05,593 --> 01:44:10,556
I have to go away soon.
I would like to see her.

1657
01:44:10,395 --> 01:44:12,897
What's the matter?
Didn't you hear me?

1658
01:44:12,795 --> 01:44:14,797
Yes, I heared you.

1659
01:44:14,716 --> 01:44:16,717
Only I'm certain sure
the devil hisself...

1660
01:44:16,636 --> 01:44:18,638
has been chasing Miss Pearl.

1661
01:44:18,557 --> 01:44:20,558
What on earth
are you talking about?

1662
01:44:20,476 --> 01:44:23,938
Mrs. McCanles, she treated
Miss Pearl awful good.

1663
01:44:23,839 --> 01:44:27,301
She treated everybody
awful good, even me.

1664
01:44:27,200 --> 01:44:30,661
And after she went to heaven...

1665
01:44:30,561 --> 01:44:33,563
Miss Pearl looks like she's had
a spell or something.

1666
01:44:33,441 --> 01:44:35,444
She wouldn't eat nothing.

1667
01:44:35,362 --> 01:44:37,363
She wouldn't talk to nobody.

1668
01:44:37,282 --> 01:44:38,784
She just stared and stared...

1669
01:44:38,723 --> 01:44:41,225
at Mrs. McCanles lying there
so still-like.

1670
01:44:41,124 --> 01:44:42,625
She ran to the barn...

1671
01:44:42,564 --> 01:44:44,816
and wouldn't come out
for nobody.

1672
01:44:44,764 --> 01:44:46,432
Poor Pearl.

1673
01:44:46,405 --> 01:44:49,866
She's sad.
I listened at the barn door...

1674
01:44:49,767 --> 01:44:51,768
and I heared her weeping
something awful.

1675
01:44:51,687 --> 01:44:53,689
I want you to do
something for me.

1676
01:44:53,607 --> 01:44:55,108
Yes?

1677
01:44:55,047 --> 01:44:57,049
Go and fix Miss Pearl
a hot breakfast.

1678
01:44:56,968 --> 01:44:58,469
Yes!

1679
01:44:58,408 --> 01:45:01,869
And I want you to pack
Miss Pearl's things.

1680
01:45:01,769 --> 01:45:04,272
Yes, ma'am! Yes, sir!

1681
01:45:07,531 --> 01:45:09,032
Go away.

1682
01:45:08,972 --> 01:45:10,598
Vashti said you wouldn't
come into the house...

1683
01:45:10,571 --> 01:45:11,990
and I couldn't believe her.

1684
01:45:11,972 --> 01:45:13,391
Leave me alone.

1685
01:45:13,373 --> 01:45:14,791
Have you gone out of your mind?

1686
01:45:14,733 --> 01:45:16,317
What are you doing out here
in the stable?

1687
01:45:16,294 --> 01:45:18,253
I bet your pa would think
it was too good for me.

1688
01:45:18,214 --> 01:45:20,175
Never mind what he thinks.
I'm not going to allow you...

1689
01:45:20,135 --> 01:45:22,762
Don't you worry none about me.
I'm going away from here.

1690
01:45:22,695 --> 01:45:26,322
- Really? Where are you going?
- It ain't your business.

1691
01:45:26,216 --> 01:45:28,176
Me and Dice
will get along all right.

1692
01:45:28,136 --> 01:45:30,097
Of course, there's Lewt.
He'll be paying a visit here...

1693
01:45:30,057 --> 01:45:32,017
sooner or later,
if I know Lewt.

1694
01:45:31,979 --> 01:45:35,440
That's right, I'm Lewt's girl.
You can't forget that, can you?

1695
01:45:35,338 --> 01:45:37,507
What makes you think that?

1696
01:45:37,460 --> 01:45:40,546
That's what you said that night.
You said you'd never forget it.

1697
01:45:40,461 --> 01:45:42,254
I did say that, didn't I?

1698
01:45:42,220 --> 01:45:45,349
It worried me sometimes
to think I'd made so much of it.

1699
01:45:45,261 --> 01:45:48,889
I hope it didn't make
any difference.

1700
01:45:48,783 --> 01:45:51,744
It didn't make no difference.

1701
01:45:51,664 --> 01:45:53,624
You're right. I'm Lewt's girl.

1702
01:45:53,584 --> 01:45:56,044
It's all I ever was.
It's all I ever could be.

1703
01:45:55,986 --> 01:45:57,946
You love him, don't you?

1704
01:45:57,905 --> 01:45:59,365
Love him? I hate him.

1705
01:45:59,345 --> 01:46:02,306
I wish they'd hang him.
I wish they'd hang him fast.

1706
01:46:02,227 --> 01:46:05,687
Yes. After all you've
been through, I suppose...

1707
01:46:05,588 --> 01:46:07,965
It ain't just his fault.

1708
01:46:09,429 --> 01:46:14,309
If he sent for me tonight,
I guess I'd go to him.

1709
01:46:14,150 --> 01:46:16,611
Lewt's not sending for you
tonight or any other night.

1710
01:46:16,550 --> 01:46:18,510
Listen, I have to be
in Paradise Flats...

1711
01:46:18,472 --> 01:46:19,932
a few days on business.

1712
01:46:19,912 --> 01:46:21,706
Do you want to wait here
until I go to Austin...

1713
01:46:21,673 --> 01:46:23,467
or would you like to
come with me right now?

1714
01:46:23,433 --> 01:46:26,227
Me? You're just
being sorry for me.

1715
01:46:26,154 --> 01:46:28,113
You don't have to be
sorry for me none!

1716
01:46:28,075 --> 01:46:30,035
Listen to me.
I won't have you thinking that.

1717
01:46:29,994 --> 01:46:31,955
It's you who are feeling
sorry for yourself.

1718
01:46:31,915 --> 01:46:35,877
I told Helen long ago
I wanted to get you out of here.

1719
01:46:35,756 --> 01:46:37,216
You told her?

1720
01:46:37,196 --> 01:46:40,157
Yes. She wants to be
your friend.

1721
01:46:40,078 --> 01:46:42,038
After your ma died...

1722
01:46:41,999 --> 01:46:44,460
I just didn't want to
go on living no more.

1723
01:46:44,399 --> 01:46:46,901
I know what you mean.

1724
01:46:48,720 --> 01:46:51,681
You'll like Helen,
and she'll like you, too.

1725
01:46:51,600 --> 01:46:53,269
You just wait and see.

1726
01:46:54,641 --> 01:46:58,437
She's a lady, ain't she?
Like your ma.

1727
01:46:58,323 --> 01:47:01,284
She's a lady,
like you're going to be.

1728
01:47:01,203 --> 01:47:03,164
No, I can't be no more.

1729
01:47:03,125 --> 01:47:05,085
Of course you can.
We'll just pretend...

1730
01:47:05,046 --> 01:47:07,005
the whole thing
was just a bad dream.

1731
01:47:06,966 --> 01:47:09,843
That's all it was actually,
a nightmare.

1732
01:47:09,766 --> 01:47:12,768
If only I could be good again!

1733
01:47:12,688 --> 01:47:15,148
Look at me.

1734
01:47:15,088 --> 01:47:17,048
Remember when you
wanted to learn...

1735
01:47:17,008 --> 01:47:19,469
when you wanted me to help you?

1736
01:47:19,408 --> 01:47:21,785
I know just the school for you.

1737
01:47:21,729 --> 01:47:22,939
School?

1738
01:47:22,929 --> 01:47:26,223
What's the matter?
Don't you still want to learn?

1739
01:47:26,132 --> 01:47:28,092
I'll do anything.

1740
01:47:28,052 --> 01:47:31,013
I'll cook for you.
I'll wash Miss Helen's clothes.

1741
01:47:30,933 --> 01:47:32,393
You'll do nothing of the sort.

1742
01:47:32,373 --> 01:47:34,834
You'll learn to waltz
and make small talk...

1743
01:47:34,773 --> 01:47:36,733
and have pretty dresses.

1744
01:47:36,695 --> 01:47:38,153
Here.

1745
01:47:40,775 --> 01:47:42,985
For me?

1746
01:47:42,936 --> 01:47:44,646
From mother to you.

1747
01:47:46,297 --> 01:47:48,757
Jesse, I...

1748
01:47:48,699 --> 01:47:50,658
I wish...

1749
01:47:52,059 --> 01:47:54,894
I wish I could die for you.

1750
01:47:56,059 --> 01:47:58,520
Let's hope you never
have to do that.

1751
01:48:28,469 --> 01:48:31,263
Is that you, Judas?

1752
01:48:31,190 --> 01:48:33,817
I got a message
from your brother...

1753
01:48:33,750 --> 01:48:36,044
the McCanles with the guts.

1754
01:48:35,992 --> 01:48:37,618
What's the matter
with the bad man?

1755
01:48:37,592 --> 01:48:39,302
Can't he deliver
his messages in person?

1756
01:48:39,273 --> 01:48:41,983
He has some business
tonight... with a train.

1757
01:48:41,913 --> 01:48:45,125
He just plumb don't like trains.

1758
01:48:45,034 --> 01:48:47,745
So I've heard.
Have you become his assistant?

1759
01:48:47,674 --> 01:48:49,634
We keep in touch
with each other.

1760
01:48:49,595 --> 01:48:51,055
You should have seen his face...

1761
01:48:51,035 --> 01:48:52,786
when I told him
you have Chavez with you.

1762
01:48:52,756 --> 01:48:54,423
I bet it was
a lovely sight to behold.

1763
01:48:54,397 --> 01:48:55,773
What's the message?

1764
01:48:55,756 --> 01:48:58,592
He says I'm to bring her
back with me... pronto.

1765
01:48:58,478 --> 01:49:02,315
Suppose she doesn't feel up
to making the trip?

1766
01:49:02,199 --> 01:49:03,951
He says if she don't
come back...

1767
01:49:03,920 --> 01:49:05,713
he's coming here
tomorrow morning...

1768
01:49:05,679 --> 01:49:07,389
bright and early and get her.

1769
01:49:08,760 --> 01:49:11,221
You seem to be
a capable messenger.

1770
01:49:11,121 --> 01:49:13,415
Would you mind
carrying back a reply?

1771
01:49:13,362 --> 01:49:15,154
Not at all. Glad to oblige.

1772
01:49:15,123 --> 01:49:18,125
You can tell my beloved brother
that I'll wait for him here.

1773
01:49:18,003 --> 01:49:21,298
I should have the sheriff
waiting for him...

1774
01:49:21,204 --> 01:49:23,165
but I prefer to meet him alone.

1775
01:49:23,125 --> 01:49:25,711
- Is that a promise?
- You're not talking to Lewt.

1776
01:49:57,174 --> 01:49:59,885
That's near enough.

1777
01:49:59,814 --> 01:50:02,192
I'm giving you one more chance.
Send Pearl out here...

1778
01:50:02,136 --> 01:50:04,137
or I'll plug you
from here to breakfast.

1779
01:50:04,097 --> 01:50:07,599
Just what do you think
Pearl's doing here with me?

1780
01:50:07,498 --> 01:50:08,958
Don't give me any...

1781
01:50:08,938 --> 01:50:11,023
of your high and mighty
noble talk, big words.

1782
01:50:10,979 --> 01:50:14,065
You think I wouldn't shoot you
because you ain't got a gun?

1783
01:50:13,980 --> 01:50:17,315
I wouldn't credit you
with any such compunctions.

1784
01:50:22,543 --> 01:50:24,586
I'm riding back
to that hitching post...

1785
01:50:24,542 --> 01:50:27,295
and then turning
and starting to shoot.

1786
01:50:27,223 --> 01:50:28,808
It's more than you did
for Sam Pierce.

1787
01:50:28,785 --> 01:50:30,245
Why all the consideration?

1788
01:50:30,225 --> 01:50:32,269
Just don't want them
fancy friends of yours...

1789
01:50:32,225 --> 01:50:35,769
to say you had a brother
who shot you down in cold blood.

1790
01:50:35,666 --> 01:50:37,208
You're going to hang.

1791
01:50:37,187 --> 01:50:41,065
You're going to hang
by the neck until you're dead!

1792
01:50:40,907 --> 01:50:42,408
You'll just go on
killing and killing...

1793
01:50:42,348 --> 01:50:45,059
till they kill you.

1794
01:50:44,988 --> 01:50:48,533
I hope Pearl gives you
a pretty funeral.

1795
01:51:07,675 --> 01:51:10,803
- Who's that?
- Just me... Lem Smoot.

1796
01:51:10,715 --> 01:51:12,509
Come here to gloat over me, huh?

1797
01:51:12,476 --> 01:51:15,605
You can turn right around
and get out of here.

1798
01:51:15,518 --> 01:51:18,479
I came because I thought maybe
you'd be needing a friend.

1799
01:51:18,399 --> 01:51:22,194
There's a funny glow in the sky
tonight, ain't there?

1800
01:51:22,079 --> 01:51:25,207
I remember once hearing
one of them Indian legends...

1801
01:51:25,120 --> 01:51:28,415
about how their ancestors
lit bonfires in the sky...

1802
01:51:28,320 --> 01:51:30,781
when a chief's son was a-dyin'.

1803
01:51:30,721 --> 01:51:32,682
He's dying?

1804
01:51:32,642 --> 01:51:34,601
It don't surprise me none.

1805
01:51:34,563 --> 01:51:37,023
Lewt always was a good shot.

1806
01:51:36,964 --> 01:51:38,924
It looks like
them ancestors of yours...

1807
01:51:38,884 --> 01:51:41,845
have to put out those bonfires.

1808
01:51:41,765 --> 01:51:43,725
What do you mean?

1809
01:51:43,685 --> 01:51:47,148
I guess Jesse's a little tougher
than you thought.

1810
01:51:47,047 --> 01:51:48,507
Thank God.

1811
01:51:48,487 --> 01:51:52,449
I thought I knew you
better than that.

1812
01:51:52,327 --> 01:51:54,788
I know how fond you were
of those boys...

1813
01:51:54,728 --> 01:51:57,148
and how proud
of them you were.

1814
01:51:57,089 --> 01:51:59,550
It don't seem possible...

1815
01:51:59,490 --> 01:52:02,451
but I must have been wrong
about a whole lot of things.

1816
01:52:02,372 --> 01:52:05,333
Laura Belle warned me
I was spoiling Lewt...

1817
01:52:05,252 --> 01:52:08,213
but I wouldn't listen to her.

1818
01:52:08,132 --> 01:52:12,386
Look. You see
them plains and hills?

1819
01:52:12,254 --> 01:52:14,088
I was so almighty proud...

1820
01:52:14,055 --> 01:52:16,348
of what I carved
out of this country.

1821
01:52:16,295 --> 01:52:18,756
I figured
I was building something...

1822
01:52:18,695 --> 01:52:20,655
for Lewt and Jesse.

1823
01:52:20,616 --> 01:52:23,076
And what have I got now?

1824
01:52:23,017 --> 01:52:26,144
Lewt a murderer, an outlaw.

1825
01:52:26,059 --> 01:52:27,267
Jesse...

1826
01:52:29,259 --> 01:52:32,678
Jesse would come back
any time you want him to.

1827
01:52:32,620 --> 01:52:35,080
You think so?

1828
01:52:35,021 --> 01:52:37,982
He told me to tell you so.

1829
01:52:40,301 --> 01:52:44,263
I'm just a lonely old man
who needs a friend...

1830
01:52:44,142 --> 01:52:46,103
like you said.

1831
01:52:52,786 --> 01:52:55,037
Whoa!

1832
01:52:59,067 --> 01:53:01,069
Here's your luggage, miss.

1833
01:53:04,709 --> 01:53:06,752
You're Miss Helen, ain't you?

1834
01:53:06,709 --> 01:53:08,587
And you're Pearl.

1835
01:53:08,551 --> 01:53:10,511
He's been asking for you.

1836
01:53:10,471 --> 01:53:12,931
How is he?

1837
01:53:12,872 --> 01:53:16,333
He's... gonna be all right.

1838
01:53:16,232 --> 01:53:18,235
Thank heaven.

1839
01:53:21,994 --> 01:53:24,955
I shouldn't cry. I know it.

1840
01:53:24,875 --> 01:53:27,335
He wouldn't like it.

1841
01:53:27,275 --> 01:53:30,777
You couldn't do nothing
he wouldn't like.

1842
01:53:33,677 --> 01:53:36,847
You're very fond
of Jesse, aren't you?

1843
01:53:40,239 --> 01:53:42,241
After my pa...

1844
01:53:44,081 --> 01:53:49,085
There wasn't never nobody
good to me like my pa...

1845
01:53:50,322 --> 01:53:53,283
Except Mrs. McCanles...

1846
01:53:53,202 --> 01:53:54,662
and Jesse.

1847
01:53:54,643 --> 01:53:56,145
My dear.

1848
01:53:57,525 --> 01:54:01,362
You will come
and live with us, won't you?

1849
01:54:02,646 --> 01:54:04,814
I want you to.

1850
01:54:10,489 --> 01:54:12,073
Yes?

1851
01:54:12,049 --> 01:54:16,094
I'm glad you and Jesse
are... bespoken.

1852
01:54:17,131 --> 01:54:18,131
Thank you.

1853
01:54:26,333 --> 01:54:28,751
Hi, Pearl.

1854
01:54:28,694 --> 01:54:30,195
How's the hero?

1855
01:54:30,174 --> 01:54:32,134
I just heard
he was gonna pull through.

1856
01:54:32,094 --> 01:54:33,554
Tough luck, ain't it?

1857
01:54:33,534 --> 01:54:36,161
But Lewt will get him next time.
You can bank on that.

1858
01:54:36,095 --> 01:54:38,889
- Next time?
- Yeah.

1859
01:54:38,815 --> 01:54:40,776
Next time.

1860
01:54:40,738 --> 01:54:43,699
I got good news for you.

1861
01:54:43,618 --> 01:54:46,079
Yeah? What is it?

1862
01:54:46,018 --> 01:54:48,229
It's from Lewt.

1863
01:54:48,179 --> 01:54:49,805
He says you got to
hightail it out of here...

1864
01:54:49,780 --> 01:54:51,406
if you want to
kiss him good-bye...

1865
01:54:51,379 --> 01:54:52,964
before he beats it
across the border.

1866
01:54:54,581 --> 01:54:57,583
You mean it? Where is he?

1867
01:54:57,461 --> 01:55:00,465
I kind of figured
you'd like that.

1868
01:55:00,343 --> 01:55:01,844
He's hiding out
at Squaw's Head Rock.

1869
01:55:01,784 --> 01:55:03,285
You got that? Squaw's Head Rock.

1870
01:55:03,224 --> 01:55:05,226
Just fire two shots
when you get there.

1871
01:55:05,145 --> 01:55:07,146
I got it. Squaw's Head Rock.

1872
01:55:07,064 --> 01:55:09,066
Take the Apache trail
to the mission.

1873
01:55:08,985 --> 01:55:11,987
Any Indian there can tell you
how to get to Buffalo Ridge.

1874
01:55:11,865 --> 01:55:13,868
And then you...
You got a good horse?

1875
01:55:13,787 --> 01:55:15,288
It's a couple of days' ride.

1876
01:55:15,227 --> 01:55:17,229
Sure. I got my pinto.

1877
01:55:17,148 --> 01:55:23,819
You know, the one Lewt gave me
before I was his girl.

1878
01:56:54,495 --> 01:56:56,455
Hiya, Pearl!

1879
01:56:57,857 --> 01:57:01,818
Here I am!
I've been waiting for you!

1880
01:57:42,469 --> 01:57:45,430
Hello, honey!
I'll be right down!

1881
01:57:45,350 --> 01:57:47,101
Stay there!

1882
01:58:00,434 --> 01:58:04,146
I can't see you!
Can you see me?

1883
01:58:32,404 --> 01:58:36,866
You... double-crossing... bobcat!

1884
01:59:09,534 --> 01:59:12,453
I guess that does it.

1885
01:59:31,381 --> 01:59:34,299
You got me that time.

1886
01:59:34,222 --> 01:59:35,723
I'm done for.

1887
01:59:35,702 --> 01:59:37,120
You're lying.

1888
01:59:38,503 --> 01:59:40,422
You're lying,
like you always do!

1889
01:59:44,265 --> 01:59:47,183
I can't shoot no more, honey.

1890
01:59:48,585 --> 01:59:50,379
Honest.

1891
01:59:50,346 --> 01:59:52,473
I'm not scared of you.

1892
01:59:52,428 --> 01:59:54,930
I'm coming up after you.

1893
01:59:54,828 --> 01:59:58,831
All right, then. Come on up!

1894
02:00:31,798 --> 02:00:34,718
No use in my...

1895
02:00:34,638 --> 02:00:36,807
lying no more.

1896
02:00:37,999 --> 02:00:39,459
I'm through.

1897
02:00:42,321 --> 02:00:44,281
You hear me?

1898
02:00:44,242 --> 02:00:45,744
Yeah.

1899
02:00:46,963 --> 02:00:48,965
I'm dying.

1900
02:00:50,324 --> 02:00:51,950
I...

1901
02:00:51,925 --> 02:00:54,384
I'm going... fast.

1902
02:00:54,325 --> 02:00:57,786
Are you...
Ain't you coming up?

1903
02:00:59,126 --> 02:01:01,795
I want to see you.
I got to see you.

1904
02:01:01,727 --> 02:01:03,519
Where are you?

1905
02:01:04,888 --> 02:01:06,889
Where are you?

1906
02:01:08,249 --> 02:01:10,210
Hurry!

1907
02:01:10,170 --> 02:01:12,506
Please!

1908
02:01:12,450 --> 02:01:15,536
I... I got to...

1909
02:01:15,450 --> 02:01:19,788
hold you... just once more.

1910
02:01:22,014 --> 02:01:24,473
I love you.

1911
02:01:25,854 --> 02:01:27,480
I love you!

1912
02:01:27,453 --> 02:01:30,331
Hurry. Hurry!

1913
02:01:32,656 --> 02:01:34,616
Hurry, honey.

1914
02:01:34,577 --> 02:01:37,037
Hold on! Hold on!

1915
02:01:36,977 --> 02:01:38,437
Hurry!

1916
02:01:38,417 --> 02:01:40,878
Wait for me!

1917
02:01:40,819 --> 02:01:42,821
Wait for me.

1918
02:01:52,342 --> 02:01:54,052
Where are you?

1919
02:02:43,677 --> 02:02:46,138
You always said you could shoot.

1920
02:02:46,077 --> 02:02:49,038
I never believed you.

1921
02:02:48,957 --> 02:02:51,918
I love you.

1922
02:02:53,119 --> 02:02:55,245
I love you.

1923
02:02:55,200 --> 02:02:57,659
Don't cry, honey.

1924
02:02:57,601 --> 02:02:59,561
Don't cry.

1925
02:02:59,520 --> 02:03:02,939
I had to do it.

1926
02:03:02,882 --> 02:03:04,842
Of course you did.

1927
02:03:04,803 --> 02:03:07,764
Let me hold you.

1928
02:03:07,684 --> 02:03:09,143
Let me...

1929
02:03:09,124 --> 02:03:12,085
Just hold me.
Hold me once more.

1930
02:03:12,005 --> 02:03:15,466
Little... bobcat.

